00:09:30.484 --> 00:09:33.387 position:19% line:83% align:start
There's a reason Pompo
chose you to be on her team.

00:09:33.420 --> 00:09:36.056 position:30% line:89% align:start
Huh? She what?

00:09:36.090 --> 00:09:38.659 position:35% line:83% align:start
 <i>PETERZEN:</i>
 <i>Look, a producer's job</i>

00:09:38.692 --> 00:09:41.261 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>is basically all about</i>
 <i>spotting talent.</i>

00:09:41.295 --> 00:09:44.565 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>Have you considered that the</i>
 <i>reason Pompo keeps you around</i>

00:09:44.598 --> 00:09:48.569 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>is because she sees</i>
 <i>something in you? Hmm?</i>

00:09:48.602 --> 00:09:52.639 position:44% line:83% align:start
GENE:
Wait. You mean really?

00:09:54.141 --> 00:09:55.476 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Hmm.
-CORVETTE: I think you're right.

00:09:55.509 --> 00:09:56.910 position:5% line:89% align:start
It would make a good adaptation.

00:09:56.944 --> 00:09:58.112 position:24% line:83% align:start
-Hey, Mr. Director.
-Hmm?

00:09:58.145 --> 00:09:59.546 position:41% line:89% align:start
A word?

00:09:59.580 --> 00:10:01.548 position:38% line:83% align:start
-(thump)
-POMPO: It's decided.

00:10:01.582 --> 00:10:04.251 position:7% line:89% align:start
That is correct, Gene, my boy.

00:10:04.284 --> 00:10:06.086 position:24% line:83% align:start
You will be cutting
the trailer for <i>Marine.</i>

00:10:06.120 --> 00:10:07.388 position:44% line:89% align:start
What?

00:10:07.421 --> 00:10:09.022 position:33% line:83% align:start
(screaming):
What?

00:10:09.056 --> 00:10:11.425 position:24% line:83% align:start
But-but-but doesn't
a producer usually hire

00:10:11.458 --> 00:10:14.061 position:19% line:83% align:start
a special trailer house
to do something like that?

00:10:14.094 --> 00:10:15.996 position:7% line:89% align:start
You want to make movies, right?

00:10:16.029 --> 00:10:17.698 position:13% line:83% align:start
Well, you got to take risks
and not do

00:10:17.731 --> 00:10:20.000 position:24% line:77% align:start
-what everyone else
usually does.
-(whimpers)

00:10:21.468 --> 00:10:24.138 position:35% line:89% align:start
(whimpers)

00:10:24.171 --> 00:10:26.073 position:35% line:89% align:start
(chuckles)

00:10:26.106 --> 00:10:29.042 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'm gonna need you
to cut a 15-second spot.

00:10:29.076 --> 00:10:31.245 position:24% line:83% align:start
You know how to use
editing software, right?

00:10:31.278 --> 00:10:33.547 position:27% line:89% align:start
Well, yes, but...

00:10:33.580 --> 00:10:36.617 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>POMPO: Grab their attention</i>
 <i>right from the top.</i>

00:10:36.650 --> 00:10:38.619 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>Give them a taste</i>
 <i>of some of the best parts,</i>

00:10:38.652 --> 00:10:41.355 position:5% line:89% align:start
 <i>but mislead them to create buzz.</i>

00:10:41.388 --> 00:10:43.323 position:16% line:89% align:start
And then end with a bang!

00:10:43.357 --> 00:10:45.459 position:21% line:89% align:start
Something like that.

00:10:45.492 --> 00:10:48.028 position:10% line:89% align:start
All that in just 15 seconds?

00:10:48.061 --> 00:10:50.564 position:24% line:83% align:start
Yep. The 15-second
trailer teaser

00:10:50.597 --> 00:10:52.533 position:35% line:83% align:start
is the spot
that most people will see,

00:10:52.566 --> 00:10:55.235 position:10% line:83% align:start
which means it also directly
affects the box office.

00:10:55.269 --> 00:10:57.671 position:19% line:83% align:start
The livelihoods of the
entire crew and their families

00:10:57.704 --> 00:11:00.007 position:10% line:83% align:start
lie solely in your hands now.
Got it?

00:11:00.040 --> 00:11:02.443 position:24% line:89% align:start
(shudders) Uh-huh.

00:11:02.476 --> 00:11:04.511 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:11:06.346 --> 00:11:08.348 position:41% line:83% align:start
 <i>GENE:</i>
 <i>It is simply impossible</i>

00:11:08.382 --> 00:11:12.486 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>to realistically fit all of that</i>
 <i>into just 15 seconds.</i>

00:11:12.519 --> 00:11:14.221 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>That's not enough time.</i>

00:11:14.254 --> 00:11:18.225 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>That's why I'm going to</i>
 <i>include outside footage.</i>

00:11:18.258 --> 00:11:20.093 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:11:24.231 --> 00:11:25.232 position:38% line:89% align:start
(grunts)

00:11:26.233 --> 00:11:28.735 position:35% line:89% align:start
(grunting)

00:11:35.108 --> 00:11:37.044 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>One technique of filmmaking</i>

00:11:37.077 --> 00:11:39.213 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>is to make the audience</i>
 <i>imagine the next scene</i>

00:11:39.246 --> 00:11:40.714 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>without showing it.</i>

00:11:45.185 --> 00:11:46.653 position:35% line:89% align:start
(grunting)

00:11:51.625 --> 00:11:53.694 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>We don't have to show</i>
 <i>everything.</i>

00:11:53.727 --> 00:11:56.363 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>I'll let the audience fill in</i>
 <i>the gaps in their heads.</i>

00:11:56.396 --> 00:11:59.099 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>I'm not even thinking</i>
 <i>about box office</i>

00:11:59.132 --> 00:12:01.535 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>or the crew's livelihoods</i>
 <i>right now</i>

00:12:01.568 --> 00:12:03.570 position:5% line:89% align:start
 <i>because I'm having too much fun!</i>

00:12:04.806 --> 00:12:06.640 position:38% line:89% align:start
(grunts)

00:12:10.477 --> 00:12:12.179 position:30% line:89% align:start
(grunts softly)

00:12:12.212 --> 00:12:14.248 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:12:20.320 --> 00:12:21.288 position:35% line:89% align:start
(chuckles)

00:12:22.556 --> 00:12:23.724 position:41% line:89% align:start
(beep)

00:12:25.492 --> 00:12:27.227 position:35% line:83% align:start
 <i>NARRATOR:</i>
 <i>It was supposed to be</i>

00:12:27.261 --> 00:12:29.096 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>another typical vacation.</i>

00:12:37.170 --> 00:12:38.105 position:38% line:89% align:start
(screams)

00:12:41.642 --> 00:12:44.044 position:13% line:89% align:start
Well? So what do you think?

00:12:45.679 --> 00:12:48.248 position:30% line:83% align:start
-Mr. Director?
-(sighs)

00:12:51.752 --> 00:12:53.754 position:38% line:83% align:start
CORVETTE:
That's Pompo, isn't it?

00:12:53.788 --> 00:12:56.623 position:24% line:5% align:start
-Yes. That's right.
-Oh!

00:12:56.657 --> 00:12:59.126 position:13% line:5% align:start
Yeah, I remember waving to
Mystia right after we wrapped.

00:12:59.159 --> 00:13:00.727 position:5% line:89% align:start
Why would you include that shot?

00:13:00.761 --> 00:13:05.399 position:24% line:83% align:start
Uh, well, I wanted
to mislead the audience

00:13:05.432 --> 00:13:07.601 position:21% line:89% align:start
to create some buzz,

00:13:07.634 --> 00:13:09.837 position:30% line:83% align:start
and I happened
to find that footage.

00:13:09.871 --> 00:13:11.806 position:19% line:89% align:start
I messed up, didn't I?

00:13:12.874 --> 00:13:14.541 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hmm.

00:13:19.246 --> 00:13:21.114 position:33% line:83% align:start
-It's great.
-(gasps softly)

00:13:21.148 --> 00:13:23.317 position:35% line:83% align:start
-I love it!
-Huh?

00:13:23.350 --> 00:13:25.485 position:19% line:83% align:start
POMPO: So Gene can make
the 30-second, two-minute,

00:13:25.519 --> 00:13:28.589 position:10% line:83% align:start
-and online versions, right?
-CORVETTE: Works for me.

00:13:28.622 --> 00:13:30.457 position:35% line:89% align:start
(chuckles)

00:13:30.490 --> 00:13:32.593 position:41% line:83% align:start
 <i>GENE:</i>
 <i>Thank you so much!</i>

00:13:32.626 --> 00:13:34.829 position:30% line:89% align:start
(clock ticking)

00:13:38.498 --> 00:13:40.167 position:41% line:89% align:start
(sighs)

00:13:42.369 --> 00:13:44.605 position:24% line:83% align:start
-POMPO: I saw you.
-Huh?

00:13:44.638 --> 00:13:46.841 position:27% line:83% align:start
You were talking
to my grandpa yesterday.

00:13:46.874 --> 00:13:48.508 position:7% line:89% align:start
You know, I didn't expect that.

00:13:48.542 --> 00:13:50.444 position:35% line:83% align:start
-(munching)
-Yeah. That's right.

00:13:50.477 --> 00:13:52.679 position:13% line:83% align:start
He said something I wanted
to ask you about.

00:13:52.713 --> 00:13:54.681 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Hmm?
-I was wondering

00:13:54.715 --> 00:13:57.451 position:30% line:83% align:start
why you decided
to make me your assistant.

00:13:57.484 --> 00:13:58.920 position:16% line:89% align:start
There are so many others.

00:13:58.953 --> 00:14:00.687 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>People who have</i>
 <i>better schooling,</i>

00:14:00.721 --> 00:14:02.322 position:24% line:89% align:start
 <i>are better-looking</i>

00:14:02.356 --> 00:14:04.191 position:33% line:83% align:start
 <i>or are just</i>
 <i>all around better than me.</i>

00:14:04.224 --> 00:14:06.526 position:5% line:89% align:start
So then what made you choose me?

00:14:06.560 --> 00:14:08.662 position:16% line:83% align:start
-Ah, that's an easy one.
-Huh?

00:14:08.695 --> 00:14:11.498 position:19% line:83% align:start
You possess one quality
that nobody else has.

00:14:14.869 --> 00:14:17.170 position:16% line:89% align:start
Your eyes don't sparkle.

00:14:17.204 --> 00:14:18.806 position:35% line:89% align:start
Huh? Uh...

00:14:18.840 --> 00:14:21.274 position:24% line:83% align:start
If you take a look
into everyone else's eyes,

00:14:21.308 --> 00:14:23.210 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>they sparkle brilliantly</i>

00:14:23.243 --> 00:14:25.646 position:30% line:83% align:start
 <i>with the hope</i>
 <i>of adolescent optimism.</i>

00:14:25.679 --> 00:14:28.515 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>But the truth is,</i>
 <i>a fulfilling life gives you</i>

00:14:28.548 --> 00:14:30.885 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>a perspective that lacks</i>
 <i>a certain depth.</i>

00:14:30.918 --> 00:14:33.620 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>And so, happiness</i>
 <i>destroys creativity.</i>

00:14:33.654 --> 00:14:35.656 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>So those others aren't</i>
 <i>qualified to be creators.</i>

00:14:35.689 --> 00:14:36.723 position:30% line:89% align:start
(buzzer blares)

00:14:38.692 --> 00:14:41.428 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>However, when I looked</i>
 <i>into your eyes,</i>

00:14:41.461 --> 00:14:43.230 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>I saw the typical signs</i>
 <i>of an outcast</i>

00:14:43.263 --> 00:14:45.766 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>with nothing going for him.</i>

00:14:45.800 --> 00:14:47.601 position:21% line:89% align:start
That's a compliment.

00:14:47.634 --> 00:14:49.837 position:30% line:89% align:start
Uh, thank you?

00:14:49.871 --> 00:14:52.606 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>POMPO: People who don't fit</i>
 <i>in the real world</i>

00:14:52.639 --> 00:14:55.709 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>create their own world</i>
 <i>inside of their mind.</i>

00:14:55.742 --> 00:14:59.413 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>The expanse and depth</i>
 <i>of an outcast's inner world is</i>

00:14:59.446 --> 00:15:02.950 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>directly correlated to their</i>
 <i>untapped creative potential.</i>

00:15:02.984 --> 00:15:06.954 position:10% line:83% align:start
And that's why I put my faith
in a complete loner like you.

00:15:06.988 --> 00:15:09.523 position:38% line:89% align:start
(gasping)

00:15:09.556 --> 00:15:11.758 position:7% line:83% align:start
-Because it's all in the eyes.
-Oh.

00:15:11.793 --> 00:15:13.393 position:41% line:83% align:start
-I see.
-(groans)

00:15:13.427 --> 00:15:15.529 position:10% line:89% align:start
Oh, no, it's happening again.

00:15:15.562 --> 00:15:17.464 position:35% line:89% align:start
(groaning)

00:15:17.497 --> 00:15:18.966 position:24% line:89% align:start
Like the other day?

00:15:19.000 --> 00:15:21.468 position:13% line:83% align:start
I feel like I'm forgetting
something.

00:15:21.501 --> 00:15:22.870 position:21% line:89% align:start
About the screening?

00:15:22.904 --> 00:15:24.771 position:35% line:89% align:start
(grumbles)

00:15:24.806 --> 00:15:26.506 position:5% line:89% align:start
Or about the audition yesterday?

00:15:26.540 --> 00:15:29.576 position:35% line:83% align:start
That's it!
Pompo remembers what it is.

00:15:29.609 --> 00:15:31.311 position:10% line:89% align:start
A little light bulb went on.

00:15:31.344 --> 00:15:34.347 position:10% line:83% align:start
I didn't notice at the time.
Here it is.

00:15:34.381 --> 00:15:35.950 position:10% line:83% align:start
-Arrange a meeting with her.
-Uh, yes, ma'am.

00:15:38.285 --> 00:15:41.388 position:30% line:89% align:start
Uh, this girl,

00:15:41.421 --> 00:15:43.457 position:19% line:83% align:start
does she have the eyes
of an outcast, too?

00:15:43.490 --> 00:15:45.793 position:21% line:83% align:start
No, 'cause an actress
needs sparkling eyes.

00:15:45.827 --> 00:15:48.896 position:5% line:89% align:start
I can't put my finger on it yet,

00:15:48.930 --> 00:15:51.364 position:35% line:83% align:start
but there's
just something about her.

00:15:51.398 --> 00:15:55.302 position:19% line:83% align:start
No matter, 'cause when
it comes to making movies,

00:15:55.335 --> 00:15:58.438 position:16% line:83% align:start
sometimes you just gotta
go with your gut, right?

00:15:58.472 --> 00:15:59.841 position:30% line:89% align:start
(gulps, grunts)

00:16:05.679 --> 00:16:08.281 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>GENE: Um, would it be okay</i>
 <i>if I used the screening room?</i>

00:16:08.315 --> 00:16:10.550 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>Sure. What you gonna watch?</i>

00:16:10.584 --> 00:16:13.386 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>Just, uh,</i> Cinema Paradiso.

00:16:13.420 --> 00:16:16.323 position:19% line:89% align:start
 <i>Ugh. I hate that one.</i>

00:16:16.356 --> 00:16:18.492 position:41% line:83% align:start
 <i>What?</i>
 <i>But that movie's a masterpiece.</i>

00:16:18.525 --> 00:16:21.028 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>Eh, it's a good story,</i>
 <i>but it's way too long.</i>

00:16:21.062 --> 00:16:23.563 position:7% line:89% align:start
So, you don't like long movies?

00:16:23.597 --> 00:16:25.298 position:27% line:89% align:start
Ugh, I hate them.

00:16:25.332 --> 00:16:27.334 position:24% line:83% align:start
But don't you think
the longer they are,

00:16:27.367 --> 00:16:28.803 position:35% line:83% align:start
the longer
you have to enjoy them?

00:16:28.836 --> 00:16:32.272 position:21% line:83% align:start
You got it all wrong.
Let me tell you a story.

00:16:34.474 --> 00:16:37.544 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>When I was a kid,</i>
 <i>my parents were always busy.</i>

00:16:37.577 --> 00:16:40.614 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>So my grandpa raised me.</i>

00:16:40.647 --> 00:16:43.985 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>And the only thing</i>
 <i>my grandpa knows are movies.</i>

00:16:44.018 --> 00:16:46.319 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>So he made me watch them.</i>

00:16:46.353 --> 00:16:48.823 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>Do you know how tough it is</i>
 <i>for a little kid to sit still</i>

00:16:48.856 --> 00:16:50.992 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>for two to three hours?</i>

00:16:51.025 --> 00:16:54.061 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>He would force me</i>
 <i>to watch the entire thing</i>

00:16:54.095 --> 00:16:56.730 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>and then make me</i>
 <i>tell him what I thought.</i>

00:16:56.763 --> 00:16:58.866 position:19% line:5% align:start
 <i>-So a simple story...</i>
-(groans)

00:16:58.900 --> 00:17:00.734 position:7% line:5% align:start
 <i>...told in 90 minutes or less</i>

00:17:00.767 --> 00:17:03.737 position:24% line:5% align:start
 <i>was like an oasis</i>
 <i>in a desert of celluloid.</i>

00:17:05.940 --> 00:17:10.077 position:7% line:83% align:start
And that is one of the reasons
why I can't stand long movies.

00:17:10.111 --> 00:17:11.444 position:41% line:83% align:start
 <i>GENE:</i>
 <i>What are the others?</i>

00:17:11.478 --> 00:17:13.047 position:16% line:89% align:start
Making people concentrate

00:17:13.080 --> 00:17:15.016 position:7% line:89% align:start
for two hours or sometimes more

00:17:15.049 --> 00:17:18.451 position:27% line:83% align:start
is simply unkind
to modern audiences.

00:17:18.485 --> 00:17:21.421 position:13% line:83% align:start
Filmmakers should recognize
that every shot is precious

00:17:21.454 --> 00:17:22.890 position:21% line:83% align:start
and attempt to convey
their vision

00:17:22.924 --> 00:17:24.391 position:16% line:89% align:start
as concisely as possible.

00:17:24.424 --> 00:17:26.994 position:19% line:83% align:start
I mean, a bloated film
isn't beautiful.

00:17:27.028 --> 00:17:28.062 position:13% line:89% align:start
It's just indulgent, yeah?

00:17:29.864 --> 00:17:32.732 position:13% line:83% align:start
But I love watching movies
so much that I don't mind

00:17:32.766 --> 00:17:35.002 position:21% line:83% align:start
sitting through three
or even four hours if...

00:17:35.036 --> 00:17:37.504 position:16% line:83% align:start
Aah! This is what's wrong
with you film buffs!

00:17:38.672 --> 00:17:40.574 position:41% line:83% align:start
 <i>GENE:</i>
 <i>Being able to pick the brain</i>

00:17:40.607 --> 00:17:42.944 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>of the one of the industry's</i>
 <i>greats from such a young age.</i>

00:17:44.678 --> 00:17:46.113 position:33% line:89% align:start
 <i>I envy her.</i>

00:17:46.147 --> 00:17:47.614 position:33% line:83% align:start
-(door opens)
-POMPO: Mind if I join you?

00:17:49.616 --> 00:17:52.485 position:16% line:83% align:start
Miss Pompo. Did you want
to watch the movie as well?

00:17:52.519 --> 00:17:54.421 position:13% line:83% align:start
It's already halfway over,
though.

00:17:54.454 --> 00:17:57.058 position:13% line:83% align:start
Great, 'cause I didn't want
to watch the whole thing.

00:17:58.793 --> 00:18:00.427 position:19% line:89% align:start
If it's a masterpiece,

00:18:00.460 --> 00:18:02.629 position:21% line:83% align:start
then checking it out
is only apropos.

00:18:02.662 --> 00:18:04.065 position:44% line:89% align:start
Um...

00:18:17.444 --> 00:18:18.612 position:41% line:83% align:start
 <i>GENE:</i>
 <i>Huh?</i>

00:18:19.847 --> 00:18:21.548 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>I'm getting déjà vu.</i>

00:18:25.552 --> 00:18:26.787 position:30% line:89% align:start
 <i>I wonder why.</i>

00:18:26.821 --> 00:18:27.855 position:35% line:89% align:start
 <i>(knocking)</i>

00:18:29.090 --> 00:18:31.158 position:7% line:89% align:start
Good morning, Miss Pompo. Huh?

00:18:33.794 --> 00:18:36.663 position:7% line:89% align:start
I guess she hasn't come in yet.

00:18:36.696 --> 00:18:37.731 position:44% line:89% align:start
Aah!

00:18:39.233 --> 00:18:41.102 position:33% line:89% align:start
(whimpering)

00:18:41.135 --> 00:18:42.870 position:30% line:89% align:start
Uh... (panting)

00:18:42.904 --> 00:18:44.839 position:41% line:5% align:start
 <i>GENE:</i>
Meister.

00:18:44.872 --> 00:18:47.041 position:13% line:5% align:start
 <i>Is this what Pompo's been</i>
 <i>working on?</i>

00:18:50.912 --> 00:18:52.079 position:41% line:89% align:start
(gulps)

00:18:54.648 --> 00:18:55.682 position:41% line:89% align:start
(gasps)

00:19:12.565 --> 00:19:15.535 position:24% line:83% align:start
Pompo has returned
from breakfast!

00:19:15.568 --> 00:19:17.038 position:24% line:83% align:start
Probably shouldn't
have eaten so much,

00:19:17.071 --> 00:19:19.539 position:30% line:83% align:start
'cause this is
one stuffed tummy.

00:19:19.572 --> 00:19:21.242 position:33% line:83% align:start
-Okay. Noted.
-How do you like the script?

00:19:21.275 --> 00:19:24.011 position:33% line:83% align:start
-Oh. Well...
-I agree. It's so true.

00:19:24.045 --> 00:19:27.014 position:16% line:83% align:start
Pompo is simply incapable
of writing a boring script.

00:19:27.048 --> 00:19:29.716 position:21% line:83% align:start
I want you to give me
a detailed analysis right now.

00:19:29.749 --> 00:19:32.719 position:16% line:89% align:start
Uh, yes. I-I can do that.

00:19:32.752 --> 00:19:35.555 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>An aging artist finds peace</i>

00:19:35.588 --> 00:19:36.824 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>when he travels</i>
 <i>to the countryside</i>

00:19:36.857 --> 00:19:38.658 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>and meets a young girl.</i>

00:19:38.692 --> 00:19:41.761 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>The story's a bit of a cliché,</i>
 <i>but that said,</i>

00:19:41.796 --> 00:19:44.764 position:7% line:83% align:start
these characters are completely
unique and compelling.

00:19:44.799 --> 00:19:47.201 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>D'Albert, the arrogant</i>
 <i>and talented conductor,</i>

00:19:47.234 --> 00:19:49.203 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>yet naive about the world.</i>

00:19:49.236 --> 00:19:52.672 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>Lily, who at times acts</i>
 <i>like an inquisitive boy</i>

00:19:52.706 --> 00:19:54.741 position:30% line:83% align:start
 <i>and at others</i>
 <i>like a sensitive girl.</i>

00:19:54.774 --> 00:19:56.944 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>These are the two</i>
 <i>main characters alone.</i>

00:19:56.978 --> 00:19:59.080 position:30% line:83% align:start
But they manage
to carry the entire film.

00:19:59.113 --> 00:20:02.615 position:10% line:83% align:start
It's incredible how a B movie
producer such as yourself

00:20:02.649 --> 00:20:04.551 position:27% line:83% align:start
managed to write
such a perfectly crafted,

00:20:04.584 --> 00:20:05.752 position:30% line:89% align:start
poignant story.

00:20:05.786 --> 00:20:07.855 position:27% line:89% align:start
Ah, I see, I see.

00:20:07.888 --> 00:20:10.724 position:10% line:83% align:start
So you think I'm nothing more
than a B movie producer?

00:20:10.757 --> 00:20:11.959 position:33% line:89% align:start
I'm so sorry!

00:20:11.993 --> 00:20:14.728 position:38% line:83% align:start
But, uh,
it's not just the story.

00:20:14.761 --> 00:20:16.763 position:19% line:83% align:start
You go from the bustle
of the city,

00:20:16.797 --> 00:20:19.934 position:21% line:83% align:start
then to the sweeping,
majestic views of the Alps.

00:20:19.967 --> 00:20:21.701 position:24% line:89% align:start
It's so liberating.

00:20:21.735 --> 00:20:24.704 position:5% line:89% align:start
If I saw that on the big screen,

00:20:24.738 --> 00:20:26.706 position:10% line:89% align:start
it would take my breath away.

00:20:26.740 --> 00:20:28.175 position:41% line:89% align:start
Mmm...

00:20:28.209 --> 00:20:31.812 position:38% line:83% align:start
-(laughs)
-(yelping)

00:20:31.846 --> 00:20:33.747 position:5% line:89% align:start
One more question for you, Gene.

00:20:33.780 --> 00:20:36.716 position:19% line:83% align:start
Out of all the scenes,
which one did you like the best?

00:20:36.750 --> 00:20:38.618 position:38% line:89% align:start
Uh, easy.

00:20:38.651 --> 00:20:40.254 position:19% line:83% align:start
It's the one where Lily
is singing

00:20:40.287 --> 00:20:41.822 position:30% line:83% align:start
and then looks
over her shoulder.

00:20:41.856 --> 00:20:44.191 position:10% line:89% align:start
Oh. That was a quick answer.

00:20:44.225 --> 00:20:45.759 position:21% line:83% align:start
Well, it's the moment
when D'Albert

00:20:45.793 --> 00:20:47.727 position:30% line:83% align:start
finally regains
his passion for music.

00:20:47.761 --> 00:20:49.797 position:16% line:89% align:start
And also when I read it,

00:20:49.830 --> 00:20:51.866 position:33% line:83% align:start
man, I could
picture it immediately.

00:20:53.167 --> 00:20:55.102 position:21% line:89% align:start
Hmm. You have passed.

00:20:55.136 --> 00:20:57.238 position:10% line:89% align:start
However, looking through it,

00:20:57.271 --> 00:20:59.907 position:7% line:83% align:start
most of these scenes only have
two actors in them,

00:20:59.940 --> 00:21:03.010 position:5% line:83% align:start
which means you're going to have
to cast really strong actors.

00:21:03.044 --> 00:21:06.347 position:10% line:83% align:start
It's already cast. We offered
D'Albert to Martin Braddock,

00:21:06.380 --> 00:21:08.182 position:24% line:89% align:start
and he's accepted.

00:21:08.215 --> 00:21:10.717 position:16% line:89% align:start
What? M-Martin Braddock?

00:21:11.886 --> 00:21:15.089 position:16% line:83% align:start
But he's a legend,
the best actor ever!

00:21:15.122 --> 00:21:18.292 position:13% line:89% align:start
Uh, wait, didn't he retire?

00:21:18.325 --> 00:21:21.328 position:13% line:83% align:start
He no longer felt inspired,
so he got more picky

00:21:21.362 --> 00:21:24.597 position:7% line:83% align:start
and hasn't said yes to anything
for ten years.

00:21:24.631 --> 00:21:26.233 position:21% line:83% align:start
That is, until I got
Grandpa to convince him.

00:21:26.267 --> 00:21:28.202 position:44% line:83% align:start
GENE:
Wow.

00:21:28.235 --> 00:21:31.005 position:16% line:83% align:start
POMPO: Martin Braddock's
first film in ten years.

00:21:31.038 --> 00:21:32.772 position:13% line:89% align:start
That'll make for great PR.

00:21:32.807 --> 00:21:35.209 position:24% line:83% align:start
This movie's gonna
be a hit now for sure.

00:21:35.242 --> 00:21:37.777 position:7% line:83% align:start
-And for Lily, we're casting...
-(door opens)

00:21:37.812 --> 00:21:40.114 position:16% line:83% align:start
-NATALIE: Um, excuse me.
-Oh? Yes. Right on cue.

00:21:40.147 --> 00:21:41.748 position:44% line:83% align:start
GENE:
Huh?

00:21:41.782 --> 00:21:43.851 position:27% line:83% align:start
I got my hair cut
just like you asked me to.

00:21:43.884 --> 00:21:45.853 position:35% line:89% align:start
How is it?

00:21:45.886 --> 00:21:48.956 position:27% line:83% align:start
POMPO: Ooh, nice.
It really suits you, Natalie.

00:21:48.989 --> 00:21:51.058 position:41% line:89% align:start
(gasps)

00:21:51.092 --> 00:21:53.794 position:35% line:83% align:start
-(screams)
-(gasps)

00:21:53.828 --> 00:21:56.763 position:30% line:83% align:start
It's-it's Lily!
I'm staring right at Lily!

00:21:56.797 --> 00:21:58.631 position:38% line:83% align:start
-I know.
-NATALIE: Huh? Huh?

00:21:58.665 --> 00:22:00.835 position:30% line:83% align:start
She's perfect.
Because I wrote it for her.

00:22:00.868 --> 00:22:03.070 position:27% line:89% align:start
That's why... Oh.

00:22:03.104 --> 00:22:05.239 position:30% line:83% align:start
The first time
I set eyes on her,

00:22:05.272 --> 00:22:07.074 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>I caught a glimmer of it.</i>

00:22:07.108 --> 00:22:10.978 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>A scene awash with a brilliant,</i>
 <i>beautiful light.</i>

00:22:11.011 --> 00:22:13.314 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>And so, in order to try</i>

00:22:13.347 --> 00:22:15.015 position:35% line:83% align:start
 <i>to capture</i>
 <i>that brief flash of light,</i>

00:22:15.049 --> 00:22:16.350 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>I wrote this script.</i>

00:22:17.318 --> 00:22:19.053 position:24% line:89% align:start
So then, sometimes,

00:22:19.086 --> 00:22:21.856 position:24% line:83% align:start
scripts are written
for specific actors?

00:22:21.889 --> 00:22:24.724 position:10% line:83% align:start
Occasionally, an entire story
will unfold in your mind

00:22:24.757 --> 00:22:26.327 position:33% line:83% align:start
when you meet
that special someone.

00:22:26.360 --> 00:22:28.028 position:7% line:89% align:start
Generally speaking, that means

00:22:28.062 --> 00:22:30.197 position:13% line:83% align:start
you have a fantastic movie
on your hands.

00:22:30.231 --> 00:22:33.000 position:41% line:83% align:start
-I see.
-NATALIE: Um, excuse me,

00:22:33.033 --> 00:22:36.303 position:16% line:83% align:start
but can you explain to me
what you two are talking about?

00:22:36.337 --> 00:22:39.173 position:41% line:83% align:start
POMPO:
I shall enlighten.

00:22:39.206 --> 00:22:41.842 position:10% line:83% align:start
Congratulations on being cast
in your first movie.

00:22:41.876 --> 00:22:44.011 position:38% line:89% align:start
Huh? Aah!

00:22:44.044 --> 00:22:47.214 position:10% line:83% align:start
W-W-W-Wait! All of a sudden?
H-H-H-How did this happen?

00:22:47.248 --> 00:22:49.083 position:19% line:77% align:start
-I don't believe this!
-Here you go.
-GENE: Huh?

00:22:49.116 --> 00:22:51.684 position:21% line:83% align:start
I'm going to let you
shoot this screenplay of mine.

00:22:51.718 --> 00:22:54.355 position:10% line:89% align:start
Best of luck, director Gene.

00:22:54.388 --> 00:22:57.892 position:27% line:89% align:start
(gasps, screams)

00:23:07.935 --> 00:23:10.471 position:10% line:83% align:start
I apologize, but we're doing
some construction up ahead.

00:23:10.504 --> 00:23:12.705 position:30% line:89% align:start
Uh, understood.

00:23:12.739 --> 00:23:15.943 position:38% line:83% align:start
This way.
Sorry for the inconvenience.

00:23:15.976 --> 00:23:17.411 position:41% line:89% align:start
(sighs)

00:23:19.413 --> 00:23:21.982 position:21% line:89% align:start
Uh, excuse me. Whoa!

00:23:23.817 --> 00:23:26.854 position:13% line:89% align:start
No, no, no, I can't sleep.

00:23:26.887 --> 00:23:30.925 position:19% line:83% align:start
I have to take a shower
and go to that audition.

00:23:35.029 --> 00:23:37.031 position:30% line:89% align:start
(gasps) Oh, no!

00:23:37.064 --> 00:23:39.266 position:38% line:89% align:start
(panting)

00:23:39.300 --> 00:23:41.068 position:24% line:89% align:start
I'm late! I'm late!

00:23:41.101 --> 00:23:43.204 position:38% line:89% align:start
(panting)

00:23:43.237 --> 00:23:44.505 position:47% line:89% align:start
Ah.

00:23:44.538 --> 00:23:46.941 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:23:46.974 --> 00:23:48.309 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hmm.

00:23:55.883 --> 00:23:58.152 position:35% line:83% align:start
Number 15!
My name's Natalie Woodward!

00:23:58.185 --> 00:23:59.486 position:21% line:89% align:start
I'm here to audition.

00:24:03.257 --> 00:24:04.525 position:35% line:89% align:start
(whimpers)

00:24:04.558 --> 00:24:07.228 position:19% line:89% align:start
(growls) No! Too plain!

00:24:07.261 --> 00:24:09.396 position:44% line:89% align:start
Aah!

00:24:11.532 --> 00:24:13.000 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>-NATALIE: That's my</i>
 <i>30th rejection.</i>

00:24:13.033 --> 00:24:14.501 position:27% line:89% align:start
-(buzzer blares)

00:24:14.535 --> 00:24:15.936 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>No wonder I'm so depressed.</i>

00:24:15.970 --> 00:24:17.137 position:30% line:89% align:start
(buzzer blares)

00:24:17.171 --> 00:24:20.773 position:24% line:89% align:start
(repeated buzzing)

00:24:24.578 --> 00:24:27.481 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>POMPO: You're late!</i>
 <i>The auditions are already over!</i>

00:24:27.514 --> 00:24:28.782 position:41% line:83% align:start
 <i>GENE:</i>
 <i>I am so sorry.</i>

00:24:30.150 --> 00:24:32.052 position:30% line:89% align:start
Too expensive.

00:24:33.988 --> 00:24:35.823 position:27% line:89% align:start
(humming softly)

00:24:43.297 --> 00:24:46.000 position:33% line:89% align:start
(whimpering)

00:24:46.033 --> 00:24:48.269 position:35% line:89% align:start
(sniffling)

00:24:56.043 --> 00:24:58.379 position:35% line:89% align:start
(laughing)

00:24:58.412 --> 00:25:01.248 position:13% line:89% align:start
My smile is my best asset,

00:25:01.282 --> 00:25:03.284 position:5% line:89% align:start
and I am never going to give up!

00:25:05.019 --> 00:25:07.154 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>I will not abandon my dreams.</i>

00:25:07.187 --> 00:25:09.423 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>It's the reason</i>
 <i>I came to this town.</i>

00:25:09.456 --> 00:25:10.991 position:30% line:83% align:start
-(phone buzzes)
-Huh?

00:25:12.393 --> 00:25:14.061 position:44% line:89% align:start
Uh...

00:25:17.298 --> 00:25:19.233 position:21% line:83% align:start
I'm here! I got here
as soon as I could!

00:25:19.266 --> 00:25:21.535 position:10% line:89% align:start
Sorry to make you rush over.

00:25:21.568 --> 00:25:24.505 position:21% line:89% align:start
Uh, Natalie Woodward.

00:25:24.538 --> 00:25:27.908 position:27% line:83% align:start
Born in Sunroad,
a town known for its corn.

00:25:27.941 --> 00:25:29.610 position:19% line:89% align:start
Zero acting experience.

00:25:29.643 --> 00:25:31.612 position:10% line:83% align:start
What are you currently doing
to make money?

00:25:31.645 --> 00:25:33.881 position:38% line:83% align:start
Oh! Well,
I have a part-time job.

00:25:33.914 --> 00:25:36.517 position:19% line:83% align:start
-How many days a week?
-Every day, I'm afraid.

00:25:36.550 --> 00:25:38.285 position:7% line:89% align:start
And are you in acting classes?

00:25:38.319 --> 00:25:40.521 position:27% line:83% align:start
I can only afford
once every two weeks.

00:25:40.554 --> 00:25:42.189 position:38% line:89% align:start
Come on.

00:25:42.222 --> 00:25:44.591 position:13% line:83% align:start
How do you expect to become
a movie star at that rate?

00:25:44.625 --> 00:25:47.528 position:35% line:77% align:start
-(whimpers)
-I assume you're familiar
with the lovely Mystia.

00:25:47.561 --> 00:25:51.165 position:10% line:83% align:start
Of course! I wish I could be
half as beautiful as she is.

00:25:51.198 --> 00:25:53.067 position:21% line:83% align:start
You're going to quit
your day job.

00:25:53.100 --> 00:25:55.069 position:44% line:77% align:start
-Huh?
-You'll also move out
of your apartment

00:25:55.102 --> 00:25:56.537 position:21% line:83% align:start
-and in with Mystia.
-Eh?

00:25:56.570 --> 00:25:58.572 position:33% line:83% align:start
From now on,
you'll be her apprentice.

00:25:58.605 --> 00:26:00.274 position:7% line:89% align:start
You will shadow her every day.

00:26:00.307 --> 00:26:02.276 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'll call her later
and give her a heads-up.

00:26:02.309 --> 00:26:05.279 position:27% line:83% align:start
You will receive
the same exact training as her,

00:26:05.312 --> 00:26:07.548 position:24% line:83% align:start
and you will learn
by observing her on set.

00:26:07.581 --> 00:26:09.583 position:33% line:83% align:start
-Understood?
-Huh? Yes.

00:26:11.518 --> 00:26:14.521 position:27% line:83% align:start
Then why are you
still standing here? Go!

00:26:14.555 --> 00:26:16.390 position:35% line:89% align:start
(screaming)

00:26:16.423 --> 00:26:18.025 position:38% line:89% align:start
(panting)

00:26:18.058 --> 00:26:19.126 position:38% line:89% align:start
(grunts)

00:26:19.159 --> 00:26:21.195 position:35% line:89% align:start
(laughing)

00:26:23.497 --> 00:26:26.433 position:24% line:89% align:start
Woo-hoo! (laughing)

00:26:26.467 --> 00:26:29.002 position:38% line:89% align:start
(gasping)

00:26:31.939 --> 00:26:33.440 position:13% line:89% align:start
Hello. You must be Natalie.

00:26:33.474 --> 00:26:35.909 position:24% line:83% align:start
-Nice to meet you.
-Uh, hi.

00:26:35.943 --> 00:26:38.178 position:24% line:89% align:start
 <i>It really is her.</i>

00:26:38.212 --> 00:26:40.381 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>She's even more beautiful</i>
 <i>in person.</i>

00:26:40.414 --> 00:26:42.950 position:19% line:89% align:start
Uh, this place is huge!

00:26:42.983 --> 00:26:46.153 position:27% line:83% align:start
I was just about
to head over to the gym.

00:26:46.186 --> 00:26:48.122 position:30% line:83% align:start
Would you like
to come along with me?

00:26:48.155 --> 00:26:49.223 position:38% line:89% align:start
Uh, yes!

00:26:49.256 --> 00:26:51.425 position:38% line:89% align:start
Oh! Whoa!

00:26:51.458 --> 00:26:54.161 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Huh?
-You have amazing abs.

00:26:54.194 --> 00:26:58.298 position:16% line:83% align:start
Yeah. I typically lay off
the workouts when I'm filming.

00:26:58.332 --> 00:27:00.934 position:21% line:83% align:start
Turns out boys aren't
that into muscles.

00:27:00.968 --> 00:27:02.269 position:41% line:89% align:start
(gasps)

00:27:03.704 --> 00:27:06.640 position:30% line:89% align:start
(grunts, sighs)

00:27:06.673 --> 00:27:09.109 position:19% line:83% align:start
That was my first time
working out.

00:27:09.143 --> 00:27:10.310 position:21% line:89% align:start
My whole body hurts.

00:27:10.344 --> 00:27:12.513 position:35% line:89% align:start
(chuckles)

00:27:14.248 --> 00:27:15.682 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hmm.

00:27:15.716 --> 00:27:18.318 position:16% line:89% align:start
Leave the cooking to me.

00:27:18.352 --> 00:27:21.088 position:5% line:89% align:start
It's the least I can do for you,

00:27:21.121 --> 00:27:23.357 position:19% line:83% align:start
and I know how to make
plenty of healthy dishes

00:27:23.390 --> 00:27:25.159 position:16% line:89% align:start
to keep you camera ready.

00:27:25.192 --> 00:27:26.560 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh.

00:27:31.098 --> 00:27:32.566 position:38% line:89% align:start
(laughs)

00:27:36.236 --> 00:27:39.306 position:10% line:83% align:start
So, Natalie, I heard that you
wanted to be an actress

00:27:39.339 --> 00:27:41.275 position:24% line:83% align:start
ever since you were
a little girl.

00:27:41.308 --> 00:27:43.210 position:13% line:89% align:start
(coughs) Yes, that's right.

00:27:43.243 --> 00:27:45.512 position:13% line:83% align:start
Well, then I hope you book
something real soon.

00:27:45.546 --> 00:27:47.047 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yeah!

00:27:49.583 --> 00:27:51.685 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>Even the smallest star</i>
 <i>in the sky</i>

00:27:51.718 --> 00:27:54.121 position:21% line:83% align:start
shines like an angel
from the heavens!

00:27:54.154 --> 00:27:56.323 position:19% line:83% align:start
No, no, no. Do you even
know what you're saying?

00:27:56.356 --> 00:27:59.193 position:7% line:83% align:start
-You sound like you're reading.
-Right! I'm so sorry.

00:28:00.294 --> 00:28:02.563 position:35% line:89% align:start
(whimpers)

00:28:02.596 --> 00:28:04.331 position:41% line:83% align:start
MYSTIA:
Here. You thirsty?

00:28:04.364 --> 00:28:06.733 position:19% line:89% align:start
Yes. Thank you so much.

00:28:06.767 --> 00:28:08.535 position:35% line:89% align:start
(chuckles)

00:28:08.569 --> 00:28:10.337 position:16% line:89% align:start
Hello! Pompo has arrived!

00:28:10.370 --> 00:28:12.406 position:24% line:89% align:start
So how's it going?

00:28:12.439 --> 00:28:13.540 position:13% line:89% align:start
Natalie, show me your face.

00:28:15.609 --> 00:28:18.245 position:19% line:89% align:start
Oh! What is she doing?

00:28:19.413 --> 00:28:21.415 position:7% line:89% align:start
Very good. She's almost ready.

00:28:21.448 --> 00:28:23.650 position:30% line:89% align:start
(shudders) Huh?

00:28:23.684 --> 00:28:27.387 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:28:27.421 --> 00:28:28.255 position:30% line:89% align:start
(buzzer blares)

00:28:32.192 --> 00:28:33.260 position:30% line:89% align:start
(buzzer blares)

00:28:43.637 --> 00:28:44.771 position:30% line:89% align:start
(buzzer blares)

00:28:44.806 --> 00:28:46.240 position:41% line:83% align:start
-(buzz)
-(ding)

00:28:49.576 --> 00:28:51.378 position:44% line:83% align:start
-♪
-(dialogue inaudible)

00:28:59.653 --> 00:29:01.355 position:41% line:83% align:start
MYSTIA:
Yes. Got it.

00:29:01.388 --> 00:29:03.257 position:30% line:89% align:start
Oh, a haircut.

00:29:03.290 --> 00:29:05.058 position:7% line:89% align:start
All right, I will let her know.

00:29:05.092 --> 00:29:07.427 position:19% line:89% align:start
Don't you worry, okay?

00:29:07.461 --> 00:29:10.430 position:10% line:83% align:start
You're finally making a move
at last, huh, Pompo?

00:29:10.464 --> 00:29:11.532 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hmm?

00:29:11.565 --> 00:29:13.467 position:33% line:89% align:start
Oh, Natalie.

00:29:13.500 --> 00:29:16.270 position:5% line:83% align:start
Miss Pompo would like to see you
at the studio tomorrow.

00:29:16.303 --> 00:29:18.138 position:38% line:83% align:start
-Also...
-Huh?

00:29:20.140 --> 00:29:22.376 position:27% line:83% align:start
I got my hair cut
just like you asked me to.

00:29:22.409 --> 00:29:24.444 position:38% line:89% align:start
(screams)

00:29:24.478 --> 00:29:27.581 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:29:27.614 --> 00:29:29.616 position:19% line:89% align:start
(grunts) Director Gene!

00:29:29.650 --> 00:29:31.552 position:24% line:89% align:start
What? The director?

00:29:31.585 --> 00:29:33.453 position:21% line:89% align:start
Oh, wait. That's me.

00:29:33.487 --> 00:29:35.857 position:30% line:83% align:start
I can't believe
this is happening to us.

00:29:35.890 --> 00:29:38.292 position:30% line:83% align:start
I feel so giddy
that I'm trying not to faint.

00:29:38.325 --> 00:29:41.295 position:30% line:83% align:start
Yeah. Me, too.
Oh, I'm so nauseous.

00:29:41.328 --> 00:29:42.396 position:33% line:83% align:start
-Hey, there.
-(whimpers)

00:29:42.429 --> 00:29:44.464 position:30% line:89% align:start
Oh! M-M-Mystia.

00:29:44.498 --> 00:29:46.166 position:16% line:83% align:start
You know, whether you two
are ready or not,

00:29:46.199 --> 00:29:47.734 position:5% line:89% align:start
this movie is going to get made.

00:29:47.768 --> 00:29:50.470 position:7% line:83% align:start
This is your chance to fulfill
your lifelong dreams.

00:29:50.504 --> 00:29:53.173 position:19% line:83% align:start
Don't just stand there.
Go out there and network.

00:29:53.206 --> 00:29:55.409 position:27% line:89% align:start
Hmm. (whimpering)

00:29:55.442 --> 00:29:57.277 position:35% line:89% align:start
Here I go!

00:29:57.311 --> 00:29:58.679 position:38% line:83% align:start
(softly):
Wow.

00:30:00.848 --> 00:30:02.749 position:7% line:89% align:start
Okay, Gene, it's your turn now.

00:30:05.185 --> 00:30:06.286 position:30% line:89% align:start
(clears throat)

00:30:06.320 --> 00:30:07.822 position:30% line:89% align:start
Hmm. (chuckles)

00:30:12.459 --> 00:30:15.295 position:16% line:83% align:start
You're Gene the director,
am I right?

00:30:17.799 --> 00:30:20.233 position:19% line:89% align:start
It's Martin. (whimpers)

00:30:20.267 --> 00:30:21.568 position:33% line:89% align:start
Best of luck.

00:30:21.602 --> 00:30:23.170 position:35% line:89% align:start
Uh, right.

00:30:23.203 --> 00:30:24.538 position:38% line:83% align:start
PETERZEN:
Thanks for doing this.

00:30:24.571 --> 00:30:26.373 position:24% line:89% align:start
Ah. There you are.

00:30:26.406 --> 00:30:28.675 position:41% line:83% align:start
 <i>GENE:</i>
 <i>I don't believe my eyes.</i>

00:30:28.709 --> 00:30:31.813 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>Two legends who, between them,</i>
 <i>have won six Nyacademy Awards</i>

00:30:31.846 --> 00:30:34.147 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>are standing right before me.</i>

00:30:34.181 --> 00:30:36.516 position:33% line:83% align:start
Good... good
to see you again, sir.

00:30:36.550 --> 00:30:38.719 position:24% line:89% align:start
Hmm? Wait a minute.

00:30:38.752 --> 00:30:40.888 position:19% line:83% align:start
You're Hawk and Animal
of the Road Warriors.

00:30:40.922 --> 00:30:42.824 position:21% line:89% align:start
I'm Gene. We've met.

00:30:42.857 --> 00:30:45.225 position:30% line:83% align:start
Yes, of course.
It's Gene, right?

00:30:45.258 --> 00:30:47.561 position:13% line:89% align:start
Congratulations, director.

00:30:47.594 --> 00:30:50.397 position:41% line:83% align:start
(gasps)
Uh, thank you so much, sir.

00:30:50.430 --> 00:30:53.533 position:16% line:83% align:start
PETERZEN: For a big star,
Martin gets lonely easily,

00:30:53.567 --> 00:30:55.636 position:10% line:89% align:start
so no need to give him space.

00:30:55.669 --> 00:30:58.505 position:19% line:83% align:start
Try to engage with him
as much as possible.

00:30:58.538 --> 00:31:00.273 position:35% line:89% align:start
Oh, right.

00:31:00.307 --> 00:31:01.909 position:38% line:83% align:start
CORVETTE:
Gene. Gene!

00:31:01.943 --> 00:31:04.244 position:19% line:89% align:start
Uh, Director Corvette.

00:31:04.277 --> 00:31:06.480 position:27% line:83% align:start
Your first movie.
Congratulations.

00:31:06.513 --> 00:31:08.415 position:41% line:83% align:start
Thanks.
And congratulations to you

00:31:08.448 --> 00:31:09.917 position:16% line:89% align:start
on the success of <i>Marine.</i>

00:31:09.951 --> 00:31:12.185 position:16% line:83% align:start
No, no. My crew deserves
all the credit.

00:31:12.219 --> 00:31:14.254 position:35% line:89% align:start
Hey, Gene,

00:31:14.287 --> 00:31:16.556 position:10% line:83% align:start
would you mind if I give you
one piece of advice?

00:31:16.590 --> 00:31:18.860 position:19% line:89% align:start
Yes. Of course you may.

00:31:18.893 --> 00:31:21.929 position:10% line:83% align:start
Since this is your first film
and Martin is your star,

00:31:21.963 --> 00:31:24.765 position:13% line:83% align:start
it means you're going to be
under a whole lot of pressure.

00:31:24.799 --> 00:31:26.500 position:7% line:89% align:start
If you try to please everyone,

00:31:26.533 --> 00:31:29.202 position:16% line:83% align:start
your movie's going to be
a directionless mess.

00:31:29.236 --> 00:31:30.938 position:13% line:89% align:start
But here's how to fix that.

00:31:30.972 --> 00:31:33.340 position:24% line:83% align:start
All you have to do
is think about the one person

00:31:33.373 --> 00:31:34.976 position:10% line:83% align:start
you want to show the movie to
the most.

00:31:35.009 --> 00:31:36.677 position:13% line:83% align:start
And as long as you make it
for them,

00:31:36.710 --> 00:31:38.880 position:19% line:83% align:start
your movie will end up
with a laser-sharp focus.

00:31:38.913 --> 00:31:41.281 position:27% line:89% align:start
That makes sense.

00:31:41.314 --> 00:31:43.450 position:16% line:83% align:start
I've been pretty worried
about screwing it all up,

00:31:43.483 --> 00:31:45.519 position:21% line:89% align:start
so that was helpful.

00:31:45.552 --> 00:31:47.254 position:35% line:83% align:start
-(chuckles)
-MARTIN: What?

00:31:47.287 --> 00:31:49.556 position:7% line:89% align:start
She's the female lead, not you?

00:31:49.589 --> 00:31:51.793 position:41% line:83% align:start
-Yeah!
-I'm actually not even in it.

00:31:51.826 --> 00:31:53.326 position:21% line:83% align:start
I'm gonna be playing
the female lead!

00:31:53.360 --> 00:31:56.229 position:7% line:89% align:start
Oh, man. What a disappointment.

00:31:56.263 --> 00:31:58.866 position:41% line:83% align:start
Anyway,
the name's Martin Braddock,

00:31:58.900 --> 00:32:00.600 position:10% line:89% align:start
the best actor in the world.

00:32:00.634 --> 00:32:02.402 position:13% line:89% align:start
Shall we exchange socials?

00:32:02.436 --> 00:32:03.905 position:13% line:83% align:start
I don't have a smartphone.
Sorry.

00:32:06.707 --> 00:32:08.742 position:27% line:89% align:start
(Natalie groans)

00:32:08.775 --> 00:32:11.611 position:13% line:83% align:start
Martin was so disappointed
that I'm the lead.

00:32:11.645 --> 00:32:13.981 position:30% line:83% align:start
Could that mean
I'm not good enough?

00:32:14.015 --> 00:32:16.283 position:30% line:83% align:start
-Director Gene.
-(gasps)

00:32:16.316 --> 00:32:17.785 position:30% line:83% align:start
I get heartburn
when I hear that.

00:32:21.388 --> 00:32:23.958 position:16% line:83% align:start
-Can I ask you something?
-Yes.

00:32:23.991 --> 00:32:27.795 position:19% line:83% align:start
Is it weird to have me
playing your female lead?

00:32:27.829 --> 00:32:30.363 position:5% line:89% align:start
Maybe I'm not attractive enough.

00:32:30.397 --> 00:32:34.735 position:41% line:83% align:start
Uh, mm,
I-I'm so nervous about this

00:32:34.768 --> 00:32:36.871 position:30% line:83% align:start
that part of me
wants to run away.

00:32:36.904 --> 00:32:39.006 position:13% line:89% align:start
But when I think about it,

00:32:39.040 --> 00:32:41.742 position:16% line:83% align:start
I'd just be running away
from reality.

00:32:41.775 --> 00:32:43.510 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>And where would I run to,</i>

00:32:43.543 --> 00:32:45.813 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>since this is the only place</i>
 <i>I belong?</i>

00:32:48.783 --> 00:32:50.617 position:10% line:89% align:start
So I only have two choices--

00:32:50.650 --> 00:32:53.487 position:19% line:83% align:start
-make the movie or die.
-(gasps)

00:32:53.520 --> 00:32:55.756 position:19% line:83% align:start
And so, I'm doing this
no matter what.

00:32:55.790 --> 00:32:58.558 position:21% line:89% align:start
I won't run. I won't.

00:32:58.592 --> 00:32:59.726 position:41% line:89% align:start
(sighs)

00:33:02.897 --> 00:33:05.532 position:38% line:83% align:start
 <i>NATALIE:</i>
 <i>Blue skies,</i>

00:33:05.565 --> 00:33:08.568 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>cornfields as far</i>
 <i>as the eye can see.</i>

00:33:10.403 --> 00:33:12.472 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>That's all there is</i>
 <i>in my hometown.</i>

00:33:13.975 --> 00:33:17.778 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>And that's the reason</i>
 <i>I loved movies so much.</i>

00:33:17.812 --> 00:33:19.780 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>They were a way</i>
 <i>for me to escape,</i>

00:33:19.814 --> 00:33:21.783 position:19% line:89% align:start
 <i>a way for me to dream.</i>

00:33:21.816 --> 00:33:24.018 position:24% line:83% align:start
One day, I'm going
to become an actress!

00:33:24.051 --> 00:33:25.853 position:35% line:89% align:start
(laughter)

00:33:27.054 --> 00:33:29.456 position:21% line:89% align:start
Don't worry, my dear.

00:33:29.489 --> 00:33:32.392 position:19% line:83% align:start
You'll make a wonderful
actress one day, Natalie.

00:33:33.760 --> 00:33:35.729 position:38% line:83% align:start
 <i>NATALIE:</i>
 <i>Ever since that day,</i>

00:33:35.762 --> 00:33:37.697 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>I worked as hard as I could.</i>

00:33:37.731 --> 00:33:39.633 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>I saved up all my money</i>

00:33:39.666 --> 00:33:41.903 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>so that I could come here</i>
 <i>to Nyallywood.</i>

00:33:41.936 --> 00:33:43.703 position:21% line:89% align:start
This is my big break.

00:33:43.737 --> 00:33:46.007 position:16% line:89% align:start
It's also my whole life.

00:33:46.040 --> 00:33:49.342 position:27% line:83% align:start
-Uh, you know...
-Yes?

00:33:49.376 --> 00:33:52.612 position:13% line:83% align:start
I just remembered something
Pompo said to me.

00:33:52.646 --> 00:33:55.817 position:21% line:83% align:start
She said, as long as
your lead actress is attractive,

00:33:55.850 --> 00:33:58.652 position:10% line:83% align:start
you've nothing to worry about
'cause your movie will be a hit.

00:33:58.685 --> 00:34:00.687 position:30% line:89% align:start
Uh-huh. Uh, mm.

00:34:00.720 --> 00:34:03.090 position:24% line:83% align:start
You were handpicked
by Pompo herself,

00:34:03.124 --> 00:34:05.059 position:21% line:89% align:start
so you're attractive

00:34:05.092 --> 00:34:06.894 position:7% line:83% align:start
'cause you're attractive enough
to be a lead actress,

00:34:06.928 --> 00:34:08.062 position:38% line:89% align:start
you know?

00:34:08.095 --> 00:34:09.729 position:41% line:89% align:start
(gasps)

00:34:09.763 --> 00:34:11.598 position:27% line:89% align:start
A-And regardless,

00:34:11.631 --> 00:34:13.868 position:19% line:83% align:start
I can't see anyone else
in the role of Lily.

00:34:13.901 --> 00:34:15.468 position:16% line:89% align:start
You don't need to worry.

00:34:15.502 --> 00:34:16.971 position:35% line:83% align:start
Just let me
take care of the rest.

00:34:17.004 --> 00:34:18.072 position:44% line:89% align:start
Uh...

00:34:18.105 --> 00:34:19.739 position:21% line:83% align:start
-(fireworks popping)
-(gasps)

00:34:19.773 --> 00:34:21.575 position:35% line:89% align:start
(whistling)

00:34:21.608 --> 00:34:23.410 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:34:27.781 --> 00:34:30.084 position:30% line:89% align:start
Mm. All right.

00:34:30.117 --> 00:34:32.854 position:10% line:89% align:start
Thank you for the confidence.

00:34:32.887 --> 00:34:35.056 position:10% line:89% align:start
Let's make a movie, director.

00:34:35.089 --> 00:34:37.058 position:38% line:89% align:start
Huh? Yes.

00:34:45.800 --> 00:34:48.135 position:35% line:83% align:start
-(snoring)
-What? You're not sleeping?

00:34:48.169 --> 00:34:50.037 position:24% line:83% align:start
Oh, well, I'm just
going over some notes

00:34:50.071 --> 00:34:52.039 position:13% line:89% align:start
from the location manager.

00:34:52.073 --> 00:34:54.041 position:5% line:89% align:start
Make sure to get plenty of rest.

00:34:54.075 --> 00:34:56.944 position:16% line:83% align:start
Don't forget, that's also
part of your job.

00:34:56.978 --> 00:34:59.113 position:24% line:89% align:start
(snoring continues)

00:35:02.616 --> 00:35:04.986 position:24% line:83% align:start
Sorry. I need to go
to the restroom.

00:35:05.019 --> 00:35:07.621 position:21% line:83% align:start
You just went, Alan.
Now you look here.

00:35:07.654 --> 00:35:09.123 position:7% line:89% align:start
This is a huge contract for us.

00:35:09.156 --> 00:35:10.858 position:13% line:89% align:start
Don't mess it up, got that?

00:35:10.892 --> 00:35:12.827 position:24% line:89% align:start
(chuckles) I won't.

00:35:13.828 --> 00:35:15.129 position:24% line:89% align:start
(scoffs) We'll see.

00:35:18.765 --> 00:35:20.134 position:41% line:89% align:start
(sighs)

00:35:33.513 --> 00:35:36.117 position:21% line:89% align:start
I know him, but how?

00:35:42.489 --> 00:35:45.226 position:16% line:5% align:start
Hello! Pompo has arrived
in Switzerland!

00:35:45.259 --> 00:35:46.559 position:30% line:89% align:start
(Natalie gasps)

00:35:46.593 --> 00:35:48.695 position:24% line:89% align:start
Oh. This is great.

00:35:48.728 --> 00:35:52.033 position:19% line:83% align:start
The despondent D'Albert
lands in Switzerland

00:35:52.066 --> 00:35:55.036 position:21% line:83% align:start
and is moved to tears
by the splendor of the Alps.

00:35:55.069 --> 00:35:56.804 position:13% line:89% align:start
That is such a great idea.

00:35:56.837 --> 00:35:57.972 position:30% line:89% align:start
I know, right?

00:35:58.005 --> 00:35:59.673 position:24% line:89% align:start
No. It won't work.

00:35:59.706 --> 00:36:00.841 position:30% line:83% align:start
-MARTIN: What?
-OTHERS: Huh?

00:36:00.875 --> 00:36:02.742 position:13% line:89% align:start
When he first arrives here,

00:36:02.776 --> 00:36:04.644 position:19% line:83% align:start
his heart is closed off
to the outside world.

00:36:04.678 --> 00:36:07.014 position:21% line:83% align:start
He's not even capable
of noticing the scenery.

00:36:07.048 --> 00:36:08.515 position:41% line:83% align:start
MARTIN:
Oh.

00:36:09.683 --> 00:36:10.918 position:44% line:89% align:start
Uh...

00:36:10.952 --> 00:36:13.054 position:35% line:89% align:start
Aah! Sorry!

00:36:13.087 --> 00:36:15.755 position:10% line:83% align:start
I have no right to challenge
any of your creative ideas!

00:36:15.790 --> 00:36:17.925 position:30% line:83% align:start
No, it's fine.
You're the director, after all.

00:36:17.959 --> 00:36:20.027 position:24% line:89% align:start
(grunts) Yes, sir.

00:36:20.061 --> 00:36:22.562 position:13% line:83% align:start
It takes a village to make
one of these little movies.

00:36:22.595 --> 00:36:25.032 position:21% line:83% align:start
Just know that I will
never hesitate

00:36:25.066 --> 00:36:26.766 position:19% line:89% align:start
to give you my opinion,

00:36:26.801 --> 00:36:28.869 position:27% line:83% align:start
and it's your job
to take it or leave it.

00:36:28.903 --> 00:36:30.770 position:35% line:89% align:start
Uh, right.

00:36:30.805 --> 00:36:33.941 position:13% line:83% align:start
Everyone, feel free to give
your creative input.

00:36:33.975 --> 00:36:35.009 position:41% line:83% align:start
-Okay.
-Got it.

00:36:35.042 --> 00:36:36.676 position:19% line:89% align:start
Ah. There are benefits

00:36:36.710 --> 00:36:39.579 position:16% line:83% align:start
to having veteran actors
in your cast.

00:36:39.612 --> 00:36:41.215 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:36:48.621 --> 00:36:51.125 position:38% line:83% align:start
 <i>NATALIE:</i>
 <i>Look how far I've come, Grandma.</i>

00:36:51.158 --> 00:36:54.795 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>And, Mystia, I'll do my best.</i>

00:36:54.829 --> 00:36:56.897 position:41% line:83% align:start
 <i>MILES:</i>
 <i>Scene 32, shot one, take one.</i>

00:36:56.931 --> 00:36:58.565 position:16% line:89% align:start
Exterior-- meadow, Alps.

00:36:58.598 --> 00:37:00.101 position:5% line:89% align:start
We see the heartbroken D'Albert.

00:37:00.134 --> 00:37:01.936 position:24% line:77% align:start
 <i>-He meets Lily for</i>
 <i>the first time.</i>
-Ready?

00:37:03.270 --> 00:37:04.604 position:41% line:89% align:start
Got it.

00:37:08.608 --> 00:37:09.743 position:41% line:83% align:start
MILES:
Rolling!

00:37:09.776 --> 00:37:10.911 position:44% line:5% align:start
GENE:
Action!

00:37:15.216 --> 00:37:17.184 position:33% line:83% align:start
-(whooshing)
-(grunts)

00:37:17.218 --> 00:37:20.287 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>GENE: This is the power</i>
 <i>of the best actor in the world.</i>

00:37:21.688 --> 00:37:23.656 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>He's usually so lively,</i>

00:37:23.690 --> 00:37:25.059 position:33% line:83% align:start
 <i>but as soon</i>
 <i>as the cameras rolled,</i>

00:37:25.092 --> 00:37:27.995 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>he embodied despondency.</i>

00:37:28.029 --> 00:37:31.198 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>However, what's even more</i>
 <i>surprising, though...</i>

00:37:33.000 --> 00:37:35.002 position:33% line:89% align:start
 <i>...is Lily.</i>

00:37:35.036 --> 00:37:38.272 position:5% line:89% align:start
 <i>Her star quality is undeniable.</i>

00:37:38.305 --> 00:37:40.041 position:19% line:83% align:start
-(explosive whooshing)
-(gasps)

00:37:42.009 --> 00:37:44.744 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>POMPO: She's perfect</i>
 <i>because I wrote it for her.</i>

00:37:44.778 --> 00:37:46.914 position:41% line:83% align:start
 <i>GENE:</i>
 <i>This is what it looks like</i>

00:37:46.947 --> 00:37:48.816 position:30% line:83% align:start
 <i>when a script</i>
 <i>is written for an actor.</i>

00:37:51.618 --> 00:37:53.788 position:21% line:89% align:start
(indistinct chatter)

00:37:53.821 --> 00:37:57.792 position:13% line:83% align:start
Uh, so, Martin, will you be
going back to Nyallywood

00:37:57.825 --> 00:38:00.294 position:10% line:83% align:start
to shoot the orchestra scene
after we're done filming here?

00:38:00.327 --> 00:38:02.096 position:27% line:89% align:start
That's the plan.

00:38:02.129 --> 00:38:04.832 position:16% line:83% align:start
Do you have to go through
conductor training or anything?

00:38:04.865 --> 00:38:06.967 position:33% line:83% align:start
-Actually...
-It's not a problem.

00:38:07.001 --> 00:38:09.636 position:10% line:83% align:start
Martin has played a conductor
twice previously.

00:38:09.669 --> 00:38:12.039 position:33% line:83% align:start
In the climax
of the film <i>Welter,</i>

00:38:12.073 --> 00:38:14.141 position:27% line:83% align:start
he had to conduct
a live, full orchestra.

00:38:14.175 --> 00:38:15.943 position:13% line:89% align:start
The scene was a single shot

00:38:15.976 --> 00:38:18.645 position:24% line:83% align:start
lasting six minutes
and 40 seconds,

00:38:18.678 --> 00:38:20.680 position:7% line:89% align:start
and it made cinematic history.

00:38:20.713 --> 00:38:23.150 position:19% line:83% align:start
Professional musicians
praised his performance,

00:38:23.184 --> 00:38:24.684 position:19% line:89% align:start
saying it was perfect.

00:38:24.717 --> 00:38:26.753 position:35% line:83% align:start
So I'm sure
he'll remember how to do it

00:38:26.787 --> 00:38:28.655 position:13% line:89% align:start
with very little coaching.

00:38:28.688 --> 00:38:29.722 position:41% line:89% align:start
(gasps)

00:38:31.358 --> 00:38:33.094 position:27% line:83% align:start
Sorry. Did I say
something wrong?

00:38:33.127 --> 00:38:35.262 position:24% line:89% align:start
Oh. I'm speechless.

00:38:35.296 --> 00:38:36.797 position:21% line:89% align:start
That's Gene for you.

00:38:36.831 --> 00:38:38.833 position:19% line:89% align:start
You really are amazing.

00:38:38.866 --> 00:38:40.801 position:24% line:83% align:start
You know everything
there is about movies.

00:38:40.835 --> 00:38:43.037 position:19% line:89% align:start
Well, it's all I have.

00:38:43.070 --> 00:38:45.339 position:7% line:89% align:start
Honestly, I'm happy and shocked

00:38:45.372 --> 00:38:47.174 position:21% line:83% align:start
that you're familiar
with one of my older films.

00:38:47.208 --> 00:38:48.843 position:21% line:89% align:start
Well, of course I am.

00:38:48.876 --> 00:38:50.177 position:38% line:83% align:start
I've seen
every one of your films.

00:38:50.211 --> 00:38:51.412 position:16% line:89% align:start
They're all masterpieces.

00:38:51.445 --> 00:38:53.147 position:27% line:89% align:start
Hmm. I like you.

00:38:53.180 --> 00:38:55.916 position:24% line:83% align:start
Let's call it a day
and drink until dawn.

00:38:55.950 --> 00:38:57.218 position:35% line:83% align:start
-Overruled.
-Aah!

00:38:59.887 --> 00:39:02.156 position:27% line:83% align:start
So let's frame it
with the sun on the right,

00:39:02.189 --> 00:39:06.026 position:7% line:83% align:start
but I also want the shot to be
a little backlit, you got that?

00:39:06.060 --> 00:39:08.329 position:21% line:83% align:start
The director's really
particular about the lighting.

00:39:08.362 --> 00:39:10.231 position:16% line:89% align:start
He's done so many setups.

00:39:10.264 --> 00:39:12.133 position:10% line:83% align:start
It's the scene where you take
D'Albert for a walk

00:39:12.166 --> 00:39:13.901 position:24% line:89% align:start
with all the goats.

00:39:13.934 --> 00:39:15.668 position:16% line:89% align:start
My guess is he just wants

00:39:15.702 --> 00:39:17.670 position:21% line:83% align:start
to do the whole thing
in a single take.

00:39:17.704 --> 00:39:19.739 position:38% line:89% align:start
Oh. Hmm?

00:39:20.908 --> 00:39:22.943 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:39:22.977 --> 00:39:24.345 position:38% line:89% align:start
(bleats)

00:39:26.113 --> 00:39:27.381 position:41% line:83% align:start
MILES:
I'm so sorry about this.

00:39:27.414 --> 00:39:30.184 position:27% line:83% align:start
The roof fell in
and spooked them.

00:39:30.217 --> 00:39:32.286 position:27% line:83% align:start
We patched it up
as best we could, but...

00:39:32.319 --> 00:39:34.321 position:21% line:83% align:start
POMPO: It was pretty
rickety to start with.

00:39:35.890 --> 00:39:38.192 position:16% line:83% align:start
But I thought there were
supposed to be more goats.

00:39:38.225 --> 00:39:41.761 position:27% line:83% align:start
-Well, you see...
-(howls)

00:39:41.795 --> 00:39:43.197 position:38% line:83% align:start
 <i>NATALIE:</i>
 <i>They were eaten by wolves?</i>

00:39:43.230 --> 00:39:45.765 position:21% line:89% align:start
(gasps) Poor things.

00:39:45.799 --> 00:39:47.700 position:16% line:83% align:start
That means we don't have
enough goats.

00:39:47.734 --> 00:39:49.470 position:24% line:83% align:start
-What do we do now?
-What did the goatherder say?

00:39:49.503 --> 00:39:51.738 position:10% line:89% align:start
It's impossible to get more.

00:39:51.771 --> 00:39:53.941 position:16% line:89% align:start
Should we postpone, then?

00:39:53.974 --> 00:39:55.476 position:7% line:83% align:start
Except we have a limited number
of shooting days

00:39:55.509 --> 00:39:56.944 position:27% line:89% align:start
at this location,

00:39:56.977 --> 00:39:58.078 position:27% line:83% align:start
and the weather's
about to change.

00:39:59.313 --> 00:40:01.015 position:41% line:83% align:start
POMPO:
And the fog's rolling in.

00:40:01.048 --> 00:40:02.349 position:38% line:89% align:start
Fog, huh?

00:40:04.818 --> 00:40:06.987 position:24% line:83% align:start
(gasps) Do we have
a smoke machine handy?

00:40:07.021 --> 00:40:09.957 position:38% line:83% align:start
-But why?
-(goat bleats)

00:40:11.926 --> 00:40:13.760 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:40:16.230 --> 00:40:18.399 position:30% line:89% align:start
(grunts, gasps)

00:40:18.432 --> 00:40:20.733 position:38% line:83% align:start
-(bleats)
-(gasps)

00:40:29.944 --> 00:40:31.778 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:40:31.812 --> 00:40:33.914 position:13% line:89% align:start
It's okay. Don't be afraid.

00:40:33.948 --> 00:40:35.916 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:40:35.950 --> 00:40:37.384 position:30% line:89% align:start
Come. This way.

00:40:43.090 --> 00:40:45.459 position:10% line:83% align:start
-The smoke was a great idea.
-Mm-hmm.

00:40:45.492 --> 00:40:47.928 position:24% line:83% align:start
And the goats were
the right amount of scary.

00:40:47.962 --> 00:40:49.897 position:24% line:5% align:start
There also ended up
being enough of them,

00:40:49.930 --> 00:40:52.099 position:16% line:5% align:start
with the cutouts we made.

00:40:52.132 --> 00:40:53.534 position:13% line:89% align:start
The script merely described

00:40:53.567 --> 00:40:54.969 position:27% line:83% align:start
D'Albert and Lily
going for a walk.

00:40:55.002 --> 00:40:57.171 position:38% line:5% align:start
(laughs)

00:40:57.204 --> 00:40:59.340 position:27% line:5% align:start
-Way to go, Gene!
-(gasps, groans)

00:40:59.373 --> 00:41:01.408 position:24% line:89% align:start
(thunder rumbling)

00:41:06.580 --> 00:41:08.549 position:41% line:83% align:start
MARTIN:
Well, today's a wash.

00:41:08.582 --> 00:41:11.118 position:16% line:5% align:start
You want to try to shoot
all the interiors instead?

00:41:11.151 --> 00:41:13.187 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:41:19.326 --> 00:41:20.995 position:27% line:89% align:start
Gene? Gene, hey!

00:41:21.028 --> 00:41:22.029 position:33% line:89% align:start
(gasps) Huh?

00:41:22.062 --> 00:41:23.464 position:27% line:89% align:start
What do you say?

00:41:23.497 --> 00:41:26.367 position:27% line:83% align:start
Uh, could I shoot
an additional scene

00:41:26.400 --> 00:41:27.501 position:16% line:89% align:start
that's not in the script?

00:41:27.534 --> 00:41:30.371 position:27% line:89% align:start
(gasps, chuckles)

00:41:30.404 --> 00:41:33.207 position:24% line:83% align:start
You're a funny guy.
You don't got to ask me.

00:41:33.240 --> 00:41:34.842 position:13% line:89% align:start
You're the boss, after all.

00:41:37.144 --> 00:41:42.049 position:16% line:83% align:start
Why do I have to do this?
This is beneath me.

00:41:42.082 --> 00:41:44.385 position:7% line:89% align:start
More working and less talking!

00:41:44.418 --> 00:41:47.354 position:13% line:83% align:start
And hurry it up before one
of the goats catches a cold!

00:41:47.388 --> 00:41:49.223 position:27% line:89% align:start
Got it! I got it!

00:41:49.256 --> 00:41:51.292 position:38% line:89% align:start
(bleats)

00:41:53.460 --> 00:41:55.229 position:41% line:83% align:start
POMPO:
Yeah. That works.

00:41:55.262 --> 00:41:57.031 position:24% line:89% align:start
It's a great scene.

00:41:57.064 --> 00:41:59.300 position:24% line:83% align:start
I also want a shot
of the rain clearing.

00:41:59.333 --> 00:42:01.135 position:16% line:89% align:start
I hope we get a rainbow.

00:42:01.168 --> 00:42:02.936 position:41% line:83% align:start
MARTIN:
Director?

00:42:02.970 --> 00:42:04.905 position:38% line:89% align:start
Uh, yes?

00:42:04.938 --> 00:42:06.974 position:24% line:83% align:start
I was going to try
falling off the roof.

00:42:07.007 --> 00:42:08.609 position:24% line:89% align:start
What do you think?

00:42:08.642 --> 00:42:10.210 position:21% line:89% align:start
I just like the idea

00:42:10.244 --> 00:42:11.845 position:24% line:83% align:start
of D'Albert getting
more humiliated.

00:42:11.879 --> 00:42:13.547 position:35% line:89% align:start
I love it!

00:42:13.580 --> 00:42:15.616 position:16% line:83% align:start
And we can even have Lily
point and laugh at him.

00:42:15.649 --> 00:42:18.085 position:13% line:83% align:start
Then D'Albert gets so angry
that he loses it

00:42:18.118 --> 00:42:19.320 position:19% line:89% align:start
and throws mud at Lily!

00:42:19.353 --> 00:42:20.621 position:47% line:89% align:start
Oh?

00:42:20.654 --> 00:42:24.391 position:27% line:83% align:start
Uh, I-I'm sorry!
I got carried away.

00:42:24.425 --> 00:42:28.529 position:19% line:83% align:start
No. It's a great idea.
I didn't expect it is all.

00:42:28.562 --> 00:42:30.531 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Huh?
-Oh, when he falls,

00:42:30.564 --> 00:42:32.466 position:19% line:83% align:start
I think he should land
in front of the door.

00:42:32.499 --> 00:42:35.269 position:10% line:83% align:start
And-and then we could have a
goat come out and lick his face.

00:42:35.302 --> 00:42:37.338 position:35% line:89% align:start
(laughter)

00:42:39.206 --> 00:42:40.341 position:27% line:83% align:start
MALE CREW MEMBER:
In that case...

00:42:40.374 --> 00:42:41.542 position:44% line:89% align:start
Wow.

00:42:41.575 --> 00:42:43.210 position:44% line:89% align:start
Aah!

00:42:43.243 --> 00:42:44.878 position:35% line:89% align:start
(splashing)

00:42:44.912 --> 00:42:46.880 position:33% line:89% align:start
(goat bleats)

00:42:46.914 --> 00:42:48.549 position:35% line:89% align:start
(screaming)

00:42:49.917 --> 00:42:50.951 position:35% line:89% align:start
(giggling)

00:42:50.984 --> 00:42:53.187 position:35% line:89% align:start
(grunting)

00:43:06.200 --> 00:43:08.335 position:38% line:89% align:start
You brat!

00:43:11.505 --> 00:43:13.006 position:21% line:89% align:start
You stuck-up windbag!

00:43:15.242 --> 00:43:16.610 position:44% line:89% align:start
Aah!

00:43:16.643 --> 00:43:18.545 position:35% line:89% align:start
(grunting)

00:43:25.519 --> 00:43:28.355 position:35% line:89% align:start
(laughing)

00:43:36.997 --> 00:43:38.165 position:35% line:89% align:start
(chuckles)

00:43:38.198 --> 00:43:39.566 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:43:39.600 --> 00:43:41.468 position:27% line:83% align:start
-Hey, look! Gene!
-(gasps)

00:43:41.502 --> 00:43:43.470 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:43:43.504 --> 00:43:46.039 position:27% line:89% align:start
Quick, shoot it!

00:43:53.213 --> 00:43:54.481 position:30% line:89% align:start
Great! And cut!

00:43:54.515 --> 00:43:55.649 position:35% line:89% align:start
(cheering)

00:43:55.682 --> 00:43:58.185 position:41% line:83% align:start
-Yeah!
-Way to go!

00:43:58.218 --> 00:44:00.454 position:27% line:83% align:start
Man, the weather
was on our side after all.

00:44:00.487 --> 00:44:02.289 position:30% line:83% align:start
That's gonna be
one killer scene!

00:44:03.190 --> 00:44:04.458 position:41% line:89% align:start
(gulps)

00:44:04.491 --> 00:44:06.493 position:7% line:89% align:start
Uh, thank you. I appreciate it.

00:44:06.527 --> 00:44:08.462 position:41% line:5% align:start
MILES:
Scene 42 is up.

00:44:08.495 --> 00:44:10.297 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>Montage, D'Albert and Lily.</i>

00:44:12.499 --> 00:44:15.169 position:44% line:83% align:start
-♪
-(dialogue inaudible)

00:44:15.202 --> 00:44:18.305 position:35% line:83% align:start
 <i>Scene 44.</i>
 <i>D'Albert learns how to fish.</i>

00:44:18.338 --> 00:44:20.574 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:44:22.543 --> 00:44:24.378 position:44% line:83% align:start
-♪
-(dialogue inaudible)

00:44:28.415 --> 00:44:32.386 position:21% line:89% align:start
(singing soft ballad)

00:44:37.558 --> 00:44:39.593 position:41% line:89% align:start
(gasps)

00:44:40.594 --> 00:44:42.529 position:24% line:89% align:start
Hold on. That song.

00:44:42.563 --> 00:44:44.598 position:24% line:89% align:start
(singing continues)

00:44:47.534 --> 00:44:49.369 position:38% line:83% align:start
-(gasps)
-(whooshing)

00:44:52.306 --> 00:44:54.208 position:35% line:89% align:start
(grunting)

00:44:54.241 --> 00:44:55.409 position:41% line:89% align:start
Pompo!

00:44:55.442 --> 00:44:57.544 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yes!

00:44:59.112 --> 00:45:01.748 position:27% line:83% align:start
This is the scene
that makes the whole movie!

00:45:03.617 --> 00:45:06.720 position:41% line:83% align:start
(sighs)
I'm completely satisfied.

00:45:06.753 --> 00:45:09.056 position:19% line:83% align:start
All right, I'll see you
back in Nyallywood.

00:45:09.089 --> 00:45:11.191 position:7% line:83% align:start
You're not staying to supervise
the rest of the shoot?

00:45:11.225 --> 00:45:14.261 position:5% line:83% align:start
I'm still working on finding you
a full orchestra.

00:45:14.294 --> 00:45:17.231 position:7% line:83% align:start
And let me tell you, it's gonna
be a scheduling nightmare.

00:45:19.099 --> 00:45:21.301 position:19% line:83% align:start
-Oh, and Gene, my boy.
-Yeah? What?

00:45:24.171 --> 00:45:27.074 position:7% line:83% align:start
This movie is gonna bring home
a Nyacademy Award,

00:45:27.107 --> 00:45:28.542 position:30% line:89% align:start
I'm sure of it.

00:45:28.575 --> 00:45:30.711 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Huh?
-Later!

00:45:30.744 --> 00:45:32.279 position:10% line:89% align:start
I leave it to you, director.

00:45:35.249 --> 00:45:36.717 position:24% line:89% align:start
(laughs nervously)

00:45:53.100 --> 00:45:54.668 position:24% line:83% align:start
FEMALE CREW MEMBER:
Stand by, please.

00:46:08.282 --> 00:46:09.583 position:38% line:89% align:start
(exhales)

00:46:09.616 --> 00:46:10.651 position:21% line:89% align:start
(dialogue inaudible)

00:46:10.684 --> 00:46:12.686 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>ALAN: It's him. The guy</i>
 <i>from the plane.</i>

00:46:18.826 --> 00:46:20.427 position:41% line:89% align:start
(gasps)

00:46:22.663 --> 00:46:24.164 position:38% line:89% align:start
(groans)

00:46:27.768 --> 00:46:29.503 position:30% line:89% align:start
Oh. Thank you.

00:46:29.536 --> 00:46:32.172 position:24% line:83% align:start
I think I know you.
You're Gene, right?

00:46:32.205 --> 00:46:34.174 position:33% line:83% align:start
You're always
writing in that book.

00:46:34.207 --> 00:46:35.342 position:35% line:89% align:start
About what?

00:46:35.375 --> 00:46:37.177 position:13% line:89% align:start
Just my thoughts on movies.

00:46:37.210 --> 00:46:38.211 position:47% line:89% align:start
Oh.

00:46:39.780 --> 00:46:41.081 position:38% line:89% align:start
(groans)

00:46:42.282 --> 00:46:44.618 position:30% line:83% align:start
(clears throat)
Here you go.

00:46:44.651 --> 00:46:47.588 position:10% line:83% align:start
Maybe you should try looking
at where you're going next time.

00:46:47.621 --> 00:46:50.290 position:16% line:83% align:start
That way, you won't drop
or lose something important.

00:46:50.324 --> 00:46:52.492 position:19% line:89% align:start
Man, what took so long?

00:46:52.526 --> 00:46:54.628 position:38% line:83% align:start
-My bad.
-(giggles)

00:46:57.799 --> 00:46:58.699 position:41% line:83% align:start
 <i>ALAN:</i>
 <i>Gene!</i>

00:46:58.732 --> 00:47:00.634 position:35% line:89% align:start
Gene Fini!

00:47:00.667 --> 00:47:02.904 position:38% line:89% align:start
Uh, huh?

00:47:02.937 --> 00:47:05.205 position:21% line:83% align:start
I thought I knew you
from somewhere.

00:47:05.238 --> 00:47:06.841 position:24% line:83% align:start
It's Alan. We went
to high school together.

00:47:08.175 --> 00:47:08.810 position:47% line:89% align:start
Oh.

00:47:14.481 --> 00:47:17.250 position:27% line:83% align:start
A movie director?
That's amazing.

00:47:17.284 --> 00:47:20.687 position:33% line:83% align:start
I can hardly
believe it myself, either.

00:47:20.721 --> 00:47:22.689 position:27% line:83% align:start
I still feel bad
about your notebook.

00:47:22.723 --> 00:47:25.626 position:33% line:83% align:start
That's okay.
I'd actually memorized it,

00:47:25.659 --> 00:47:27.461 position:21% line:83% align:start
so I just rewrote it
in a new one.

00:47:27.494 --> 00:47:29.596 position:44% line:89% align:start
Uh...

00:47:29.630 --> 00:47:31.698 position:16% line:89% align:start
So what do you do, Alan?

00:47:31.732 --> 00:47:32.900 position:44% line:89% align:start
Uh...

00:47:35.435 --> 00:47:39.272 position:24% line:83% align:start
"Nyallywood Bank."
Oh, wow. That's major.

00:47:39.306 --> 00:47:40.774 position:16% line:83% align:start
-No, it sucks. I hate it.
-Uh...

00:47:49.282 --> 00:47:51.184 position:24% line:89% align:start
Again, I apologize.

00:47:51.218 --> 00:47:53.888 position:33% line:83% align:start
I had no idea
that he hated golf, sir.

00:47:53.921 --> 00:47:56.456 position:13% line:89% align:start
"Sorry" doesn't fix things.

00:47:57.624 --> 00:48:00.260 position:10% line:83% align:start
If you were on the ball, you
would've researched the client.

00:48:00.293 --> 00:48:03.263 position:35% line:83% align:start
It's basic.
I expect more from an intern.

00:48:03.296 --> 00:48:04.832 position:27% line:83% align:start
You may have been
a hotshot analyst,

00:48:04.866 --> 00:48:06.299 position:10% line:89% align:start
but you're an associate now.

00:48:06.333 --> 00:48:08.502 position:7% line:89% align:start
You can't coast on by anymore.

00:48:08.535 --> 00:48:10.838 position:13% line:83% align:start
-You have to do real work.
-I'm sorry, sir.

00:48:10.872 --> 00:48:12.406 position:38% line:89% align:start
(scoffs)

00:48:21.816 --> 00:48:24.217 position:7% line:83% align:start
(sighs) Lately, I've even been
considering quitting.

00:48:24.251 --> 00:48:25.719 position:38% line:89% align:start
But why?

00:48:25.752 --> 00:48:28.956 position:24% line:83% align:start
I've never had any
real ambitions or goals.

00:48:28.990 --> 00:48:31.558 position:21% line:83% align:start
Everything just came
naturally to me.

00:48:31.591 --> 00:48:34.661 position:33% line:83% align:start
But real life
is nothing like high school.

00:48:34.695 --> 00:48:38.265 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>It's harsher. And everything</i>
 <i>slips into nothingness.</i>

00:48:40.267 --> 00:48:41.869 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Huh.
-(phone buzzes)

00:48:41.903 --> 00:48:44.604 position:16% line:89% align:start
Oh. Uh, sorry. Uh, hello?

00:48:45.639 --> 00:48:47.441 position:35% line:89% align:start
Understood.

00:48:47.474 --> 00:48:49.776 position:27% line:89% align:start
I, uh, gotta run.

00:48:49.811 --> 00:48:52.579 position:7% line:83% align:start
Uh, let me know when your movie
comes out, and I'll go see it.

00:48:52.612 --> 00:48:55.615 position:7% line:83% align:start
-And, uh, thanks for the chat.
-Yeah, likewise.

00:49:00.487 --> 00:49:02.689 position:21% line:83% align:start
You know what, Gene?
I take it back. I was wrong.

00:49:04.959 --> 00:49:07.327 position:38% line:83% align:start
You were
looking ahead all along.

00:49:07.360 --> 00:49:09.596 position:21% line:83% align:start
I can see the sparkle
in your eyes now.

00:49:09.629 --> 00:49:10.664 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:49:14.836 --> 00:49:17.939 position:10% line:89% align:start
Is it true? My eyes sparkle?

00:49:22.810 --> 00:49:23.978 position:38% line:89% align:start
(grunts)

00:49:25.947 --> 00:49:27.614 position:38% line:89% align:start
(groans)

00:49:27.647 --> 00:49:28.816 position:30% line:89% align:start
Nice, and cut!

00:49:28.850 --> 00:49:31.651 position:16% line:89% align:start
We did it! That's a wrap!

00:49:31.685 --> 00:49:33.821 position:19% line:89% align:start
(cheering and applause)

00:49:35.722 --> 00:49:37.724 position:19% line:89% align:start
Now time to celebrate!

00:49:37.758 --> 00:49:40.027 position:38% line:89% align:start
(weeping)

00:49:40.061 --> 00:49:43.965 position:10% line:83% align:start
Oh, Grandma, you were right.
I did it! Huh?

00:49:46.366 --> 00:49:50.805 position:7% line:83% align:start
Mr. Director! Thank you so much
for all your support!

00:49:50.838 --> 00:49:51.906 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:49:53.373 --> 00:49:55.675 position:41% line:83% align:start
-Uh...
-And then, yeah.

00:49:55.709 --> 00:49:57.044 position:44% line:89% align:start
Uh...

00:49:57.078 --> 00:49:59.013 position:30% line:89% align:start
Director Gene?

00:49:59.046 --> 00:50:01.414 position:27% line:83% align:start
The actors' work
may be all done,

00:50:01.448 --> 00:50:03.785 position:13% line:83% align:start
but for our boy Gene here,
it's only just beginning.

00:50:03.818 --> 00:50:04.919 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:50:04.952 --> 00:50:06.854 position:24% line:89% align:start
(laughs nervously)

00:50:08.622 --> 00:50:09.924 position:38% line:83% align:start
 <i>NATALIE:</i>
 <i>Oh, right.</i>

00:50:09.957 --> 00:50:12.526 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>It still needs to be edited.</i>

00:50:12.559 --> 00:50:14.996 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>POMPO: Editing is the most vital</i>
 <i>part of a film.</i>

00:50:15.029 --> 00:50:17.564 position:5% line:89% align:start
 <i>Everything's riding on Gene now.</i>

00:50:17.597 --> 00:50:20.034 position:38% line:83% align:start
 <i>MARTIN:</i>
 <i>He's editing his own movie?</i>

00:50:20.067 --> 00:50:22.435 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>That's not typical</i>
 <i>for a director.</i>

00:50:22.469 --> 00:50:24.604 position:41% line:83% align:start
 <i>POMPO:</i>
 <i>I always have my directors</i>

00:50:24.638 --> 00:50:26.808 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>do it themselves</i>
 <i>if they can, but...</i>

00:50:26.841 --> 00:50:28.976 position:35% line:83% align:start
-But what?
-You see,

00:50:29.010 --> 00:50:31.411 position:16% line:83% align:start
this film has the makings
of a masterpiece.

00:50:31.444 --> 00:50:34.414 position:19% line:83% align:start
However, the editor is
the first test audience.

00:50:34.447 --> 00:50:37.852 position:16% line:83% align:start
Directing is subjective,
but editing is objective.

00:50:37.885 --> 00:50:40.720 position:16% line:83% align:start
So now does our Gene have
what it takes

00:50:40.754 --> 00:50:43.825 position:13% line:83% align:start
to bridge that gap and find
the perfect cut, I wonder.

00:50:43.858 --> 00:50:44.892 position:41% line:89% align:start
(gasps)

00:50:46.961 --> 00:50:48.461 position:41% line:83% align:start
 <i>GENE:</i>
 <i>Time to edit.</i>

00:50:48.495 --> 00:50:50.764 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>This is gonna be so much fun.</i>

00:50:52.033 --> 00:50:53.633 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>I must be the happiest person</i>

00:50:53.667 --> 00:50:56.037 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>on the face of the earth</i>
 <i>right now.</i>

00:50:56.070 --> 00:50:59.073 position:5% line:89% align:start
 <i>We shot about 72 hours of film,</i>

00:50:59.106 --> 00:51:02.609 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>but now what do I do with it?</i>

00:51:02.642 --> 00:51:05.046 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>I'm making a movie</i>
 <i>starring Martin Braddock.</i>

00:51:05.079 --> 00:51:07.114 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>It needs to be impressive.</i>

00:51:07.148 --> 00:51:09.382 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>I need a lot of depth</i>
 <i>right at the start,</i>

00:51:09.416 --> 00:51:10.584 position:27% line:89% align:start
 <i>lots of fanfare.</i>

00:51:10.617 --> 00:51:14.454 position:16% line:89% align:start
(playing classical music)

00:51:31.671 --> 00:51:33.607 position:7% line:89% align:start
(music continues over computer)

00:51:33.640 --> 00:51:36.610 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>I'm not going to show</i>
 <i>the whole concert.</i>

00:51:36.643 --> 00:51:39.113 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>I'll jump-cut to the next scene</i>
 <i>before the audience gets bored.</i>

00:51:40.447 --> 00:51:42.049 position:27% line:89% align:start
(music continues)

00:51:46.087 --> 00:51:47.922 position:24% line:89% align:start
Evening, D'Albert.

00:51:47.955 --> 00:51:50.490 position:19% line:83% align:start
Masterful performance,
my friend.

00:51:50.523 --> 00:51:51.926 position:41% line:83% align:start
 <i>GENE:</i>
 <i>Scene 12--</i>

00:51:51.959 --> 00:51:54.427 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>interior, the concert hall's</i>
 <i>green room.</i>

00:51:54.461 --> 00:51:56.931 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>We shot eight different</i>
 <i>camera angles.</i>

00:51:56.964 --> 00:51:59.133 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>I'll line them up</i>
 <i>chronologically.</i>

00:52:00.734 --> 00:52:02.435 position:24% line:89% align:start
Evening, D'Albert.

00:52:02.469 --> 00:52:04.071 position:19% line:83% align:start
Masterful performance,
my friend.

00:52:04.105 --> 00:52:06.173 position:38% line:83% align:start
D'ALBERT:
Don't patronize me.

00:52:06.207 --> 00:52:08.876 position:10% line:83% align:start
I'm gonna need you to find me
a better flautist, Coltman.

00:52:08.910 --> 00:52:11.812 position:7% line:83% align:start
COLTMAN: Let me ask you, do you
have any idea what she costs?

00:52:11.846 --> 00:52:14.514 position:24% line:83% align:start
And let me ask you,
who am I to you?

00:52:15.715 --> 00:52:17.550 position:24% line:89% align:start
The great D'Albert.

00:52:17.584 --> 00:52:20.221 position:19% line:83% align:start
That said, if your next
concert is a success,

00:52:20.254 --> 00:52:22.223 position:33% line:83% align:start
you'll become
an international legend.

00:52:22.256 --> 00:52:24.091 position:24% line:89% align:start
This I promise you.

00:52:24.125 --> 00:52:25.927 position:10% line:89% align:start
I'm doing <i>St Matthew Passion.</i>

00:52:25.960 --> 00:52:27.694 position:24% line:89% align:start
Huh? Are you sure?

00:52:27.727 --> 00:52:29.864 position:5% line:89% align:start
Do you have a problem with that?

00:52:29.897 --> 00:52:32.967 position:10% line:83% align:start
Well, with you conducting it,
I'm sure it'll be perfect--

00:52:33.000 --> 00:52:34.869 position:7% line:89% align:start
technically speaking, at least.

00:52:34.902 --> 00:52:37.838 position:10% line:83% align:start
But a <i>Passion</i> requires, well,
you know, actual passion.

00:52:37.872 --> 00:52:40.174 position:19% line:89% align:start
Which I can't provide?

00:52:40.207 --> 00:52:44.011 position:27% line:83% align:start
I ask you again,
who am I to you?

00:52:46.147 --> 00:52:48.182 position:41% line:89% align:start
(sighs)

00:52:49.549 --> 00:52:52.153 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>GENE: There's nothing but</i>
 <i>exposition in this scene.</i>

00:52:52.987 --> 00:52:54.654 position:27% line:89% align:start
 <i>Let's try this.</i>

00:52:54.688 --> 00:52:56.623 position:30% line:89% align:start
(music resumes)

00:52:59.559 --> 00:53:01.896 position:24% line:89% align:start
Don't patronize me.

00:53:01.929 --> 00:53:04.799 position:10% line:83% align:start
I'm gonna need you to find me
a better flautist, Coltman.

00:53:04.832 --> 00:53:07.534 position:13% line:83% align:start
Let me ask you, do you have
any idea what she costs?

00:53:07.567 --> 00:53:10.503 position:24% line:83% align:start
And let me ask you,
who am I to you?

00:53:10.537 --> 00:53:12.840 position:41% line:83% align:start
 <i>GENE:</i>
 <i>I'll start with the wide shots.</i>

00:53:12.873 --> 00:53:15.977 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>That'll create a sense</i>
 <i>of mystery surrounding D'Albert.</i>

00:53:16.010 --> 00:53:18.611 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>And by emphasizing Martin's</i>
 <i>emotionless delivery,</i>

00:53:18.645 --> 00:53:20.915 position:30% line:83% align:start
 <i>it'll increase</i>
 <i>the tension of the scene.</i>

00:53:20.948 --> 00:53:24.517 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>Ordinarily, one would transition</i>
 <i>to a medium shot here,</i>

00:53:24.551 --> 00:53:25.886 position:30% line:83% align:start
 <i>but I'm gonna</i>
 <i>rattle the audience</i>

00:53:25.920 --> 00:53:28.255 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>by jumping straight</i>
 <i>to the close-up.</i>

00:53:28.289 --> 00:53:32.059 position:27% line:83% align:start
I ask you again,
who am I to you?

00:53:32.093 --> 00:53:33.928 position:41% line:83% align:start
 <i>GENE:</i>
 <i>That's it.</i>

00:53:33.961 --> 00:53:36.563 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>This shows off D'Albert's</i>
 <i>prickly personality.</i>

00:53:36.596 --> 00:53:39.133 position:5% line:89% align:start
 <i>I'll keep employing this tactic.</i>

00:53:42.803 --> 00:53:46.073 position:35% line:83% align:start
 <i>Scene 24,</i>
 <i>page 20 of the screenplay.</i>

00:53:46.107 --> 00:53:48.976 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>D'Albert finally leaves</i>
 <i>for Switzerland.</i>

00:53:49.010 --> 00:53:52.279 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>But it's taken 90 minutes</i>
 <i>of story just to get here.</i>

00:53:52.313 --> 00:53:54.949 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>And what's worse,</i>
 <i>we won't get to meet Lily</i>

00:53:54.982 --> 00:53:56.784 position:5% line:89% align:start
 <i>for another 30 minutes at least.</i>

00:53:58.119 --> 00:54:00.988 position:24% line:89% align:start
 <i>How do I fix this?</i>

00:54:01.022 --> 00:54:04.758 position:33% line:83% align:start
What? Pompo's
in Australia right now?

00:54:04.792 --> 00:54:06.827 position:13% line:89% align:start
Yes. She's currently there

00:54:06.861 --> 00:54:08.996 position:19% line:83% align:start
scouting for locations
with director Corvette.

00:54:09.030 --> 00:54:11.165 position:13% line:89% align:start
How long will she be gone?

00:54:11.198 --> 00:54:12.867 position:10% line:89% align:start
For about another two weeks.

00:54:12.900 --> 00:54:14.935 position:35% line:89% align:start
Oh. I see.

00:54:14.969 --> 00:54:18.205 position:5% line:89% align:start
Uh, she did leave you a message.

00:54:18.239 --> 00:54:19.706 position:38% line:89% align:start
She did?

00:54:19.739 --> 00:54:21.608 position:30% line:89% align:start
(clears throat)

00:54:21.641 --> 00:54:23.277 position:24% line:83% align:start
(imitating Pompo):
I expect to see the final cut

00:54:23.310 --> 00:54:25.212 position:35% line:83% align:start
in my inbox
as soon as I get back!

00:54:25.246 --> 00:54:27.948 position:21% line:89% align:start
So don't let me down.

00:54:27.982 --> 00:54:29.616 position:30% line:83% align:start
(normal voice):
That was the whole message.

00:54:29.649 --> 00:54:30.284 position:35% line:89% align:start
(whimpers)

00:54:32.685 --> 00:54:34.088 position:41% line:83% align:start
 <i>GENE:</i>
 <i>I don't have a choice.</i>

00:54:34.121 --> 00:54:36.290 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>I have to start over</i>
 <i>from the top.</i>

00:54:39.260 --> 00:54:40.995 position:35% line:83% align:start
(echoing):
Evening, D'Albert.

00:54:41.028 --> 00:54:42.963 position:19% line:83% align:start
Masterful performance,
my friend.

00:54:42.997 --> 00:54:45.299 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:54:47.268 --> 00:54:49.270 position:19% line:89% align:start
(overlapping dialogue)

00:54:56.877 --> 00:54:59.313 position:13% line:83% align:start
D'ALBERT: Do you even know
how to read music?

00:54:59.346 --> 00:55:01.681 position:38% line:83% align:start
(grunts)
Again from the top!

00:55:03.417 --> 00:55:05.286 position:7% line:89% align:start
I want the orchestra replaced!

00:55:05.319 --> 00:55:07.121 position:16% line:83% align:start
Have you lost your mind,
D'Albert?

00:55:07.154 --> 00:55:10.157 position:10% line:89% align:start
The concert is in two weeks.

00:55:10.191 --> 00:55:12.393 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>How am I supposed to find that</i>
 <i>many musicians that quickly?</i>

00:55:12.426 --> 00:55:14.661 position:19% line:89% align:start
 <i>(overlapping dialogue)</i>

00:55:16.097 --> 00:55:19.834 position:21% line:83% align:start
Just answer me this--
what does this aria mean to you?

00:55:23.304 --> 00:55:25.039 position:19% line:89% align:start
(overlapping dialogue)

00:55:27.274 --> 00:55:29.910 position:10% line:89% align:start
I quit, D'Albert. I'm sorry.

00:55:29.944 --> 00:55:31.912 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>You brought this on yourself.</i>

00:55:31.946 --> 00:55:33.247 position:30% line:89% align:start
(phone clicks)

00:55:48.162 --> 00:55:50.364 position:38% line:89% align:start
(grunts)

00:55:56.370 --> 00:55:58.205 position:35% line:89% align:start
(grunting)

00:55:59.373 --> 00:56:01.342 position:38% line:89% align:start
(panting)

00:56:01.375 --> 00:56:03.110 position:19% line:89% align:start
(overlapping dialogue)

00:56:18.225 --> 00:56:20.727 position:5% line:89% align:start
You've grown careless, D'Albert.

00:56:21.929 --> 00:56:23.364 position:16% line:83% align:start
You didn't even bother
to lock your door.

00:56:26.100 --> 00:56:27.234 position:35% line:89% align:start
(straining)

00:56:31.405 --> 00:56:33.706 position:19% line:89% align:start
You and I have history.

00:56:33.740 --> 00:56:36.443 position:10% line:83% align:start
Actually, I feel responsible
for what's happened.

00:56:36.477 --> 00:56:41.182 position:7% line:83% align:start
How many years has it been now
since your wife and kid left?

00:56:42.782 --> 00:56:45.419 position:35% line:83% align:start
Why are you
bringing that up now?

00:56:45.452 --> 00:56:47.121 position:27% line:89% align:start
(Coltman exhales)

00:56:47.154 --> 00:56:49.890 position:30% line:83% align:start
Maybe it's time
you took a break.

00:56:49.924 --> 00:56:52.725 position:19% line:83% align:start
Get away. Use it to do
some self-reflection.

00:57:05.339 --> 00:57:09.776 position:16% line:83% align:start
What am I without music?
Nothing.

00:57:10.978 --> 00:57:12.779 position:38% line:89% align:start
(grunts)

00:57:14.114 --> 00:57:15.449 position:24% line:89% align:start
It's Mr. Peterzen.

00:57:23.190 --> 00:57:25.259 position:24% line:89% align:start
Uh, excuse me, sir.

00:57:25.292 --> 00:57:26.460 position:44% line:89% align:start
Whoa.

00:57:37.271 --> 00:57:40.307 position:30% line:89% align:start
Huh. (chuckles)

00:57:48.983 --> 00:57:51.252 position:38% line:89% align:start
Hmm. Huh?

00:57:51.285 --> 00:57:53.854 position:21% line:89% align:start
Oh. Aren't you the...

00:57:53.887 --> 00:57:55.322 position:35% line:89% align:start
It's Gene.

00:57:55.356 --> 00:57:57.925 position:24% line:83% align:start
I, uh, didn't mean
to disturb you.

00:57:57.958 --> 00:57:59.827 position:19% line:89% align:start
But what are you doing?

00:57:59.860 --> 00:58:02.429 position:30% line:83% align:start
Just having fun
with some old film.

00:58:04.064 --> 00:58:07.201 position:38% line:83% align:start
Amazing.
That's an actual film splicer.

00:58:07.234 --> 00:58:10.404 position:35% line:83% align:start
(chuckles)
It's an old man's hobby,

00:58:10.437 --> 00:58:14.441 position:16% line:83% align:start
trying to create a story
from discarded film

00:58:14.475 --> 00:58:16.944 position:16% line:89% align:start
by piecing them together.

00:58:16.977 --> 00:58:19.480 position:35% line:89% align:start
Huh. Uh...

00:58:19.513 --> 00:58:22.249 position:19% line:83% align:start
-Um, I was wondering...
-Uh-huh?

00:58:24.318 --> 00:58:25.953 position:38% line:83% align:start
PETERZEN:
Hmm.

00:58:25.986 --> 00:58:28.889 position:7% line:89% align:start
All the scenes feel important,

00:58:28.922 --> 00:58:31.492 position:30% line:83% align:start
and they're all
wonderful performances.

00:58:31.525 --> 00:58:35.062 position:16% line:83% align:start
But I have to cut a ton,
or it'll be too long.

00:58:35.095 --> 00:58:38.198 position:38% line:83% align:start
Tell me,
why don't you ask Pompo?

00:58:38.232 --> 00:58:40.301 position:33% line:89% align:start
Uh... (sighs)

00:58:40.334 --> 00:58:42.202 position:41% line:89% align:start
well...

00:58:42.236 --> 00:58:46.140 position:24% line:83% align:start
I get it. Pompo is
the screenwriter, isn't she?

00:58:48.042 --> 00:58:51.011 position:27% line:83% align:start
What's the point
of you editing the movie

00:58:51.045 --> 00:58:53.314 position:24% line:83% align:start
if you can only do
what she tells you to?

00:58:53.347 --> 00:58:54.381 position:41% line:89% align:start
Right.

00:58:57.084 --> 00:58:59.253 position:41% line:83% align:start
-Gene.
-Huh?

00:58:59.286 --> 00:59:02.022 position:38% line:83% align:start
PETERZEN:
Who do we make movies for?

00:59:02.056 --> 00:59:05.492 position:5% line:89% align:start
Well, for the audience, I guess.

00:59:06.927 --> 00:59:09.063 position:35% line:83% align:start
And, Gene,
what is it about movies

00:59:09.096 --> 00:59:10.431 position:19% line:89% align:start
that you love so much?

00:59:10.464 --> 00:59:12.633 position:44% line:89% align:start
Uh...

00:59:12.666 --> 00:59:15.402 position:19% line:83% align:start
I'm guessing you found
yourself in them.

00:59:15.436 --> 00:59:17.404 position:19% line:89% align:start
Does that sound right?

00:59:17.438 --> 00:59:22.943 position:10% line:83% align:start
Through them, you experienced
empathy, dreams, longing.

00:59:22.976 --> 00:59:25.279 position:21% line:89% align:start
You experienced life.

00:59:25.312 --> 00:59:28.248 position:24% line:89% align:start
Now, tell me, Gene,

00:59:28.282 --> 00:59:31.552 position:19% line:83% align:start
have you found yourself
in your movie yet?

00:59:36.156 --> 00:59:38.092 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hmm.

00:59:38.125 --> 00:59:39.560 position:35% line:83% align:start
 <i>PETERZEN:</i>
 <i>Once you have,</i>

00:59:39.593 --> 00:59:41.428 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>you'll find your passion.</i>

00:59:41.462 --> 00:59:44.565 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>Put it in your film</i>
 <i>like you would an aria.</i>

00:59:49.136 --> 00:59:50.938 position:41% line:83% align:start
 <i>GENE:</i>
 <i>What's my aria?</i>

00:59:50.971 --> 00:59:52.439 position:44% line:83% align:start
LILY:
What?

00:59:52.473 --> 00:59:54.441 position:21% line:83% align:start
You've never strolled
through the mountains before?

00:59:54.475 --> 00:59:57.244 position:19% line:83% align:start
And how will doing that
enhance my music?

00:59:57.277 --> 00:59:59.546 position:33% line:89% align:start
Uh... (sighs)

01:00:01.315 --> 01:00:04.451 position:35% line:83% align:start
 <i>PETERZEN:</i>
 <i>An aria is a musical solo</i>

01:00:04.485 --> 01:00:06.620 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>used to express emotion.</i>

01:00:06.653 --> 01:00:08.322 position:38% line:83% align:start
D'ALBERT:
Back home, they worship me.

01:00:08.355 --> 01:00:10.657 position:21% line:83% align:start
I devoted everything
I had to music.

01:00:12.126 --> 01:00:13.293 position:33% line:89% align:start
But for who?

01:00:13.327 --> 01:00:14.995 position:44% line:89% align:start
Uh...

01:00:15.028 --> 01:00:17.498 position:30% line:89% align:start
(gasps, sighs)

01:00:17.531 --> 01:00:20.968 position:27% line:83% align:start
So ask yourself,
what are you trying to express?

01:00:21.001 --> 01:00:24.605 position:27% line:83% align:start
But also, to whom
do you want to express it?

01:00:26.273 --> 01:00:28.609 position:27% line:83% align:start
Do you even know
how to read music? (grunts)

01:00:28.642 --> 01:00:31.044 position:24% line:89% align:start
Again from the top!

01:00:31.078 --> 01:00:33.614 position:19% line:83% align:start
What's wrong? You think
you're better than the score?

01:00:33.647 --> 01:00:35.616 position:35% line:83% align:start
Is that why
you're not following it?

01:00:35.649 --> 01:00:38.352 position:19% line:83% align:start
No. But if you want me
to keep playing,

01:00:38.385 --> 01:00:41.622 position:21% line:83% align:start
just answer me this--
what does this aria mean to you?

01:00:41.655 --> 01:00:43.056 position:41% line:89% align:start
(gasps)

01:00:44.324 --> 01:00:45.959 position:35% line:89% align:start
That's it.

01:00:47.628 --> 01:00:51.465 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>(Lily singing soft ballad)</i>

01:00:51.498 --> 01:00:53.333 position:35% line:89% align:start
I found it.

01:00:53.367 --> 01:00:57.271 position:24% line:89% align:start
(continues singing)

01:00:57.304 --> 01:01:00.374 position:19% line:89% align:start
Uh, hold on. That song.

01:01:22.429 --> 01:01:25.265 position:21% line:89% align:start
(film reel rattling)

01:01:30.537 --> 01:01:32.473 position:27% line:89% align:start
It's me. It's me.

01:01:32.506 --> 01:01:35.542 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

01:01:46.220 --> 01:01:49.289 position:10% line:89% align:start
Wait a minute. That means...

01:01:51.358 --> 01:01:54.328 position:33% line:83% align:start
Do not fear,
for Pompo has returned!

01:01:54.361 --> 01:01:56.330 position:16% line:89% align:start
Uh, I'm glad you're back.

01:01:56.363 --> 01:01:58.599 position:35% line:83% align:start
Okay, Gene,
I want to see the film.

01:01:58.632 --> 01:02:00.634 position:7% line:89% align:start
Well, it isn't quite finished.

01:02:02.369 --> 01:02:04.538 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Huh?
-It isn't quite finished.

01:02:04.571 --> 01:02:06.373 position:19% line:89% align:start
Could you repeat that?

01:02:06.406 --> 01:02:08.509 position:16% line:83% align:start
-It isn't quite finished.
-How long is it?

01:02:08.542 --> 01:02:10.511 position:10% line:89% align:start
I started over from scratch,

01:02:10.544 --> 01:02:13.213 position:13% line:83% align:start
and there's about 72 hours
of footage left.

01:02:16.450 --> 01:02:19.186 position:30% line:89% align:start
Well, explain.

01:02:19.219 --> 01:02:20.788 position:16% line:83% align:start
Our very first screening
is scheduled

01:02:20.822 --> 01:02:22.556 position:19% line:89% align:start
for two weeks from now,

01:02:22.589 --> 01:02:24.391 position:19% line:83% align:start
and all of our sponsors
will be there.

01:02:24.424 --> 01:02:26.660 position:10% line:83% align:start
They're going to pull funding
if it isn't ready.

01:02:26.693 --> 01:02:29.363 position:16% line:83% align:start
So you had better give me
a damn good reason

01:02:29.396 --> 01:02:31.632 position:19% line:83% align:start
-for this delay, Gene.
-It's missing something.

01:02:32.633 --> 01:02:34.368 position:41% line:83% align:start
-Uh...
-Hmm?

01:02:34.401 --> 01:02:36.804 position:38% line:83% align:start
-A scene.
-Huh?

01:02:36.838 --> 01:02:39.206 position:41% line:89% align:start
(gasps)

01:02:39.239 --> 01:02:42.509 position:13% line:83% align:start
Are you telling me you want
to do additional shooting?

01:02:42.543 --> 01:02:45.279 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Yes.
-(thump)

01:02:45.312 --> 01:02:48.315 position:24% line:83% align:start
POMPO: As I'm sure
you're already aware,

01:02:48.348 --> 01:02:51.853 position:19% line:83% align:start
additional shoots means
reassembling the entire crew.

01:02:51.886 --> 01:02:55.656 position:19% line:83% align:start
Now, Gene, do you have
any idea how hard that is?

01:02:55.689 --> 01:02:57.457 position:30% line:89% align:start
I can imagine.

01:02:57.491 --> 01:02:59.726 position:30% line:83% align:start
You need a crew
in order to make a movie,

01:02:59.760 --> 01:03:02.462 position:7% line:83% align:start
but most of them have moved on
to other projects by now,

01:03:02.496 --> 01:03:05.766 position:10% line:83% align:start
which means calling in favors
and rescheduling other shoots.

01:03:05.800 --> 01:03:07.668 position:27% line:83% align:start
Who do you think
pays for that, huh, Gene?

01:03:07.701 --> 01:03:09.136 position:33% line:89% align:start
You do, miss.

01:03:09.169 --> 01:03:11.438 position:21% line:83% align:start
And getting your cast
to come back

01:03:11.471 --> 01:03:13.173 position:10% line:89% align:start
is an even bigger nightmare.

01:03:13.206 --> 01:03:15.475 position:27% line:83% align:start
Who do you think
negotiates that, huh, Gene?

01:03:15.509 --> 01:03:16.643 position:33% line:89% align:start
You do, miss.

01:03:16.677 --> 01:03:18.579 position:5% line:89% align:start
Lastly, who wrote the screenplay

01:03:18.612 --> 01:03:20.113 position:33% line:83% align:start
that you feel
is missing a scene?

01:03:20.147 --> 01:03:22.516 position:30% line:83% align:start
-You did, miss.
-Now I ask you again,

01:03:22.549 --> 01:03:25.752 position:13% line:83% align:start
are you telling me you want
to do additional shooting?

01:03:26.788 --> 01:03:27.654 position:41% line:89% align:start
(sighs)

01:03:29.857 --> 01:03:31.491 position:13% line:89% align:start
Where is this coming from?

01:03:31.525 --> 01:03:34.194 position:19% line:83% align:start
Because quite frankly,
I think it's insane.

01:03:34.227 --> 01:03:36.697 position:10% line:83% align:start
You actually want to attempt
that aria again?

01:03:36.730 --> 01:03:38.365 position:38% line:89% align:start
(scoffs)

01:03:39.533 --> 01:03:40.868 position:33% line:89% align:start
(clattering)

01:03:43.270 --> 01:03:46.640 position:21% line:83% align:start
D'Albert, you're only
embarrassing yourself.

01:03:46.673 --> 01:03:48.508 position:19% line:89% align:start
I never understood it.

01:03:48.542 --> 01:03:50.577 position:7% line:89% align:start
No. I'd somehow forgotten it--

01:03:50.611 --> 01:03:52.779 position:24% line:89% align:start
 <i>the smell of fish</i>

01:03:52.814 --> 01:03:54.816 position:35% line:83% align:start
or the pain
of slipping in the rain.

01:03:54.849 --> 01:03:56.617 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>Even the bleating of goats.</i>

01:03:56.650 --> 01:03:59.219 position:30% line:89% align:start
Uh, what? Stop.

01:03:59.252 --> 01:04:01.388 position:24% line:83% align:start
Emotions, memories.
They're important,

01:04:01.421 --> 01:04:03.323 position:24% line:83% align:start
and that young girl
reminded me of that.

01:04:03.357 --> 01:04:06.560 position:16% line:83% align:start
I know I can do the piece
justice now.

01:04:06.593 --> 01:04:09.563 position:41% line:83% align:start
(sighs)
Face it, you're all washed up.

01:04:09.596 --> 01:04:11.632 position:24% line:83% align:start
Why don't you just
give up already?

01:04:11.665 --> 01:04:14.802 position:13% line:5% align:start
 <i>D'ALBERT: Because in spite</i>
 <i>of everything...</i>

01:04:14.836 --> 01:04:16.904 position:44% line:5% align:start
GENE:
This is all I have. My art.

01:04:16.938 --> 01:04:19.306 position:21% line:83% align:start
-D'ALBERT: And so...
-GENE: Please...

01:04:19.339 --> 01:04:22.576 position:24% line:83% align:start
-My music needs...
-My movie needs...

01:04:22.609 --> 01:04:24.745 position:10% line:83% align:start
-...another shot at the aria.
-...another scene for the film.

01:04:24.778 --> 01:04:25.880 position:35% line:89% align:start
I beg you!

01:04:25.913 --> 01:04:27.748 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

01:04:33.955 --> 01:04:35.155 position:41% line:89% align:start
Pompo?

01:04:39.794 --> 01:04:41.896 position:41% line:83% align:start
POMPO:
Fine. I'll see what I can do.

01:04:41.929 --> 01:04:43.697 position:38% line:89% align:start
(exhales)

01:04:44.899 --> 01:04:47.567 position:35% line:83% align:start
-(chuckles)
-(laughs nervously)

01:04:47.601 --> 01:04:49.369 position:33% line:89% align:start
Unbelievable.

01:04:49.403 --> 01:04:51.238 position:16% line:83% align:start
I never dreamed that kid
would challenge me.

01:04:51.271 --> 01:04:53.206 position:19% line:83% align:start
Why does he have to be
so stubborn?

01:04:53.240 --> 01:04:55.308 position:21% line:89% align:start
(chuckles) And yet...

01:04:55.342 --> 01:04:57.544 position:38% line:83% align:start
CORVETTE:
I've never seen you happier.

01:05:12.994 --> 01:05:15.328 position:13% line:89% align:start
Oh. Alan. What do you want?

01:05:15.362 --> 01:05:19.266 position:35% line:83% align:start
Well, sir,
I've just been thinking

01:05:19.299 --> 01:05:21.201 position:27% line:89% align:start
that this job...

01:05:24.371 --> 01:05:26.306 position:16% line:89% align:start
Wait. What is this thing?

01:05:26.339 --> 01:05:27.774 position:33% line:83% align:start
Hey. Who said
you could take that?

01:05:29.911 --> 01:05:31.946 position:13% line:83% align:start
It's an investment proposal
for a film.

01:05:31.979 --> 01:05:34.281 position:41% line:83% align:start
-Uh...
-I was just about to call them

01:05:34.314 --> 01:05:35.749 position:21% line:83% align:start
to say that we aren't
interested.

01:05:35.782 --> 01:05:37.350 position:21% line:89% align:start
Wait. You're passing?

01:05:37.384 --> 01:05:39.787 position:41% line:5% align:start
 <i>BOSS:</i>
 <i>They canceled their screening</i>

01:05:39.821 --> 01:05:42.522 position:7% line:5% align:start
 <i>because the director couldn't</i>
 <i>finish the edit in time,</i>

01:05:42.556 --> 01:05:45.492 position:19% line:5% align:start
 <i>so all their sponsors</i>
 <i>pulled out.</i>

01:05:45.525 --> 01:05:47.661 position:38% line:83% align:start
-(gasps)
-Investing in movies

01:05:47.694 --> 01:05:49.997 position:10% line:89% align:start
is a very high-risk venture.

01:05:50.031 --> 01:05:52.666 position:13% line:83% align:start
What if the director never
manages to complete the film?

01:05:55.435 --> 01:05:59.439 position:24% line:83% align:start
Sir, give it to me,
and I'll manage the account.

01:05:59.473 --> 01:06:01.675 position:35% line:89% align:start
Huh? Uh...

01:06:07.347 --> 01:06:09.951 position:33% line:83% align:start
-POMPO: Well?
-GENE: It-it's perfect.

01:06:09.984 --> 01:06:12.854 position:16% line:83% align:start
I never thought I'd have
to write an additional scene

01:06:12.887 --> 01:06:15.555 position:27% line:83% align:start
-at your request.
-I'm so sorry.

01:06:15.589 --> 01:06:17.357 position:30% line:83% align:start
I just thought
it'd be more consistent

01:06:17.390 --> 01:06:18.926 position:5% line:89% align:start
if you were the one to write it.

01:06:18.960 --> 01:06:20.694 position:10% line:89% align:start
I guess all directors end up

01:06:20.727 --> 01:06:23.497 position:19% line:83% align:start
as arrogant and selfish
as you're being.

01:06:23.530 --> 01:06:27.367 position:13% line:83% align:start
But who are you gonna cast
in this brand-new part?

01:06:27.400 --> 01:06:29.837 position:24% line:83% align:start
We don't have time
to hold any auditions.

01:06:29.871 --> 01:06:33.640 position:10% line:83% align:start
Well, uh, actually, I already
have someone perfect in mind.

01:06:36.443 --> 01:06:37.677 position:41% line:83% align:start
MYSTIA:
Hmm?

01:06:37.711 --> 01:06:39.312 position:24% line:89% align:start
The <i>Meister</i> script?

01:06:39.346 --> 01:06:41.381 position:41% line:83% align:start
Uh-huh.
Yeah, that's right.

01:06:41.414 --> 01:06:44.051 position:16% line:83% align:start
It's a new draft because
they added one more scene.

01:06:44.085 --> 01:06:45.820 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh.

01:06:45.853 --> 01:06:48.956 position:10% line:5% align:start
But our sponsors pulled out,
so without additional funding,

01:06:48.990 --> 01:06:51.625 position:10% line:5% align:start
we won't be able to shoot it.

01:06:51.658 --> 01:06:54.962 position:21% line:83% align:start
Actors are powerless
in these kinds of situations.

01:06:54.996 --> 01:06:56.596 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

01:06:56.630 --> 01:06:58.431 position:7% line:89% align:start
"You can't have both, D'Albert.

01:06:58.465 --> 01:07:02.435 position:13% line:83% align:start
Allow me to just say this.
Your music..."

01:07:02.469 --> 01:07:04.972 position:24% line:89% align:start
Uh, Mystia? Hello?

01:07:05.006 --> 01:07:08.976 position:30% line:83% align:start
Huh? Oh, sorry.
Here.

01:07:09.010 --> 01:07:10.845 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Huh?
-(chuckles)

01:07:15.049 --> 01:07:17.450 position:41% line:83% align:start
POMPO:
Ah, this is awful.

01:07:17.484 --> 01:07:20.988 position:19% line:83% align:start
How on earth am I gonna
market this thing?

01:07:21.022 --> 01:07:23.590 position:30% line:83% align:start
-(phone rings)
-Hello. Peterzen Film.

01:07:24.758 --> 01:07:28.461 position:33% line:83% align:start
Alan Gardner
from Nyallywood Bank?

01:07:28.495 --> 01:07:30.630 position:5% line:89% align:start
Your bank didn't get back to us.

01:07:30.664 --> 01:07:33.000 position:19% line:83% align:start
I assumed they rejected
our proposal.

01:07:33.034 --> 01:07:35.569 position:5% line:89% align:start
Well, technically, the bank has.

01:07:35.602 --> 01:07:37.470 position:35% line:89% align:start
However...

01:07:37.504 --> 01:07:38.738 position:41% line:89% align:start
(gasps)

01:07:53.120 --> 01:07:54.487 position:38% line:89% align:start
You sure?

01:07:55.689 --> 01:07:56.523 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yes.

01:07:57.992 --> 01:07:58.926 position:19% line:89% align:start
(chuckles) That's good.

01:08:00.660 --> 01:08:02.729 position:21% line:83% align:start
You prepared to lose
everything if you fail?

01:08:02.762 --> 01:08:03.798 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yes.

01:08:06.868 --> 01:08:10.004 position:19% line:83% align:start
Then welcome to a world
of dreams and madness.

01:08:20.815 --> 01:08:22.083 position:41% line:89% align:start
(sighs)

01:08:23.650 --> 01:08:24.952 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

01:08:28.789 --> 01:08:30.624 position:16% line:89% align:start
This could get you fired.

01:08:32.827 --> 01:08:36.496 position:5% line:89% align:start
There's no success without risk.

01:08:36.529 --> 01:08:38.866 position:33% line:83% align:start
-Am I right?
-Yeah, but still...

01:08:45.806 --> 01:08:48.541 position:19% line:77% align:start
-Send me what you have,
and I'll help.
-Huh?

01:08:48.575 --> 01:08:51.145 position:13% line:83% align:start
You won't be ready in time
at this rate.

01:08:54.248 --> 01:08:56.516 position:38% line:89% align:start
(typing)

01:09:03.757 --> 01:09:07.028 position:24% line:83% align:start
And so, I recommend
that we invest in <i>Meister.</i>

01:09:07.061 --> 01:09:10.965 position:10% line:83% align:start
(sighs) Even with a big star
like Martin attached,

01:09:10.998 --> 01:09:12.166 position:24% line:89% align:start
the director's new.

01:09:12.199 --> 01:09:13.901 position:16% line:89% align:start
It also doesn't bode well

01:09:13.935 --> 01:09:15.635 position:19% line:83% align:start
that the film's gotten
bad press,

01:09:15.669 --> 01:09:17.872 position:16% line:83% align:start
which makes it too risky
in my book.

01:09:17.905 --> 01:09:19.006 position:19% line:89% align:start
I vote we don't invest.

01:09:20.207 --> 01:09:20.841 position:41% line:89% align:start
(sighs)

01:09:23.210 --> 01:09:24.744 position:7% line:89% align:start
The meeting's adjourned, then.

01:09:26.914 --> 01:09:28.916 position:24% line:83% align:start
I haven't finished
my presentation yet!

01:09:29.951 --> 01:09:30.985 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Hmm?
-Huh?

01:09:34.688 --> 01:09:38.125 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>I've always been good</i>
 <i>at embodying my characters.</i>

01:09:38.159 --> 01:09:39.726 position:21% line:5% align:start
Some say it's a gift.

01:09:39.759 --> 01:09:41.228 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

01:09:41.262 --> 01:09:44.564 position:19% line:5% align:start
Yes, it's been my dream
since I was a girl.

01:09:44.597 --> 01:09:46.666 position:27% line:5% align:start
I must've watched
thousands of movies

01:09:46.700 --> 01:09:49.236 position:5% line:5% align:start
with my grandpa as a little kid.
But you know what?

01:09:49.270 --> 01:09:52.006 position:16% line:5% align:start
Not a single one of them
has ever truly moved me.

01:09:52.039 --> 01:09:55.675 position:10% line:5% align:start
So, then, is that what you're
trying do with this movie?

01:09:55.709 --> 01:09:57.744 position:27% line:83% align:start
Except I can't be
the one to make it.

01:09:57.777 --> 01:10:00.547 position:19% line:83% align:start
Because then I wouldn't
be able to enjoy it. See?

01:10:00.580 --> 01:10:02.515 position:13% line:89% align:start
That's where Gene comes in.

01:10:02.549 --> 01:10:04.751 position:19% line:83% align:start
It's why you hired him
to direct it.

01:10:04.785 --> 01:10:09.056 position:10% line:83% align:start
'Cause out of all the movies,
this one is your dream.

01:10:09.090 --> 01:10:11.058 position:21% line:5% align:start
So how long has this
been your dream?

01:10:11.092 --> 01:10:12.492 position:35% line:5% align:start
Well, uh...

01:10:14.795 --> 01:10:18.933 position:13% line:83% align:start
I've always loved watching
movies ever since I was a kid.

01:10:21.634 --> 01:10:25.239 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>I didn't have any friends,</i>
 <i>but I didn't really care.</i>

01:10:25.272 --> 01:10:28.809 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>I mean, there were</i>
 <i>so many movies to watch,</i>

01:10:28.843 --> 01:10:31.078 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>so many I hadn't seen yet.</i>

01:10:32.813 --> 01:10:34.581 position:19% line:83% align:start
-But there was a girl.
-(gasps)

01:10:35.782 --> 01:10:38.752 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>In every theater I went to,</i>
 <i>she was there.</i>

01:10:38.786 --> 01:10:41.222 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>She never stayed, though.</i>

01:10:41.255 --> 01:10:43.224 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>She always left</i>
 <i>when the end credits began.</i>

01:10:45.092 --> 01:10:47.194 position:5% line:89% align:start
 <i>I can't even remember her face.</i>

01:10:48.229 --> 01:10:50.931 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>But I always wondered...</i>

01:10:50.965 --> 01:10:53.666 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>what was it that drew her</i>
 <i>to the movies?</i>

01:10:55.269 --> 01:10:57.704 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>And had she never been</i>
 <i>so engrossed in a film</i>

01:10:57.737 --> 01:10:59.773 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>that she wanted to stay</i>
 <i>till the end,</i>

01:10:59.807 --> 01:11:01.242 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>until after the credits</i>
 <i>had rolled?</i>

01:11:06.113 --> 01:11:07.815 position:19% line:89% align:start
 <i>When I think about it,</i>

01:11:07.848 --> 01:11:10.184 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>it's the reason I wanted</i>
 <i>to make a movie myself.</i>

01:11:11.218 --> 01:11:13.988 position:27% line:89% align:start
 <i>Movies saved me.</i>

01:11:14.021 --> 01:11:17.158 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>So maybe someone else</i>
 <i>will be saved by mine.</i>

01:11:19.026 --> 01:11:22.329 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>And then I finally saw it--</i>
 <i>myself in the movie.</i>

01:11:23.964 --> 01:11:25.866 position:30% line:89% align:start
 <i>This movie...</i>

01:11:25.900 --> 01:11:28.169 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>I made it for the me</i>
 <i>all those years ago.</i>

01:11:29.769 --> 01:11:31.806 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>No, not just for me.</i>

01:11:33.007 --> 01:11:35.843 position:13% line:89% align:start
(song playing in Japanese)

01:11:41.048 --> 01:11:42.817 position:41% line:83% align:start
 <i>ALAN:</i>
 <i>I see.</i>

01:11:42.850 --> 01:11:45.019 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>It needed a character</i>
 <i>that everyone can identify with.</i>

01:11:45.052 --> 01:11:47.021 position:33% line:83% align:start
 <i>Someone who,</i>
 <i>no matter who watches it,</i>

01:11:47.054 --> 01:11:49.023 position:27% line:89% align:start
 <i>can believe in.</i>

01:11:49.056 --> 01:11:50.391 position:44% line:83% align:start
GENE:
It's what helped me realize

01:11:50.424 --> 01:11:53.693 position:13% line:83% align:start
that the movie was lacking
a very important scene.

01:11:53.726 --> 01:11:55.830 position:16% line:83% align:start
One little crucial scene
it required

01:11:55.863 --> 01:11:57.198 position:16% line:83% align:start
that would make the movie
complete.

01:11:59.166 --> 01:12:01.035 position:16% line:89% align:start
To show what we sacrifice

01:12:01.068 --> 01:12:03.170 position:24% line:83% align:start
in order to be able
to pursue our dreams.

01:12:03.204 --> 01:12:05.172 position:24% line:89% align:start
 <i>And so I beg you,</i>

01:12:05.206 --> 01:12:07.308 position:5% line:89% align:start
 <i>please make my dreams come true.</i>

01:12:10.211 --> 01:12:12.847 position:19% line:83% align:start
ALAN: You know, things
always came naturally,

01:12:12.880 --> 01:12:15.648 position:7% line:83% align:start
and I succeeded at everything,
or so I thought.

01:12:15.682 --> 01:12:17.351 position:16% line:89% align:start
But, looking back at it,

01:12:17.384 --> 01:12:19.253 position:21% line:83% align:start
what have I actually
accomplished?

01:12:19.286 --> 01:12:21.688 position:10% line:83% align:start
What's the point of anything
if it doesn't have meaning?

01:12:21.721 --> 01:12:24.757 position:30% line:83% align:start
And once I came
to that realization,

01:12:24.792 --> 01:12:27.694 position:21% line:83% align:start
I knew I had to find
something for myself.

01:12:27.727 --> 01:12:30.064 position:35% line:83% align:start
I ask you,
what is a banker's job really

01:12:30.097 --> 01:12:32.933 position:7% line:83% align:start
if not to give people the means
to fulfill their dreams?

01:12:32.967 --> 01:12:34.667 position:35% line:89% align:start
So please!

01:12:34.701 --> 01:12:36.837 position:19% line:83% align:start
We want to make a movie
that will give people

01:12:36.871 --> 01:12:39.440 position:19% line:83% align:start
who have nothing a way
to keep on dreaming!

01:12:39.473 --> 01:12:42.843 position:10% line:89% align:start
(song continues in Japanese)

01:12:42.877 --> 01:12:45.112 position:35% line:83% align:start
I'll admit,
I agree with what you've said.

01:12:45.146 --> 01:12:48.082 position:30% line:83% align:start
That is exactly
what bankers ought to do.

01:12:48.115 --> 01:12:51.085 position:13% line:83% align:start
But we can't make decisions
based on philosophy.

01:12:51.118 --> 01:12:53.686 position:19% line:83% align:start
You need to convince us
with concrete figures,

01:12:53.720 --> 01:12:54.955 position:19% line:89% align:start
not just nice stories.

01:12:56.123 --> 01:12:58.092 position:44% line:83% align:start
ALAN:
Figures.

01:12:58.125 --> 01:12:59.960 position:10% line:89% align:start
(song continues in Japanese)

01:13:04.899 --> 01:13:07.700 position:10% line:83% align:start
-ALAN: I have those figures.
-You do?

01:13:10.237 --> 01:13:12.940 position:33% line:83% align:start
-What's this?
-You've been filming us?

01:13:12.973 --> 01:13:15.142 position:30% line:83% align:start
I do apologize,
but not only that,

01:13:15.176 --> 01:13:17.945 position:16% line:83% align:start
I've been streaming this
entire meeting worldwide.

01:13:17.978 --> 01:13:19.280 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Huh?
-What?

01:13:25.486 --> 01:13:28.088 position:24% line:83% align:start
Our documentary is
also available online.

01:13:28.122 --> 01:13:30.090 position:30% line:89% align:start
What's more...

01:13:30.124 --> 01:13:31.859 position:19% line:89% align:start
You're crowdfunding it?

01:13:31.892 --> 01:13:33.994 position:19% line:83% align:start
ALAN: We launched this
website a few days ago.

01:13:34.028 --> 01:13:36.964 position:13% line:83% align:start
This was how much we raised
on the very first day,

01:13:36.997 --> 01:13:39.400 position:16% line:89% align:start
and this is the fund now.

01:13:39.433 --> 01:13:42.436 position:24% line:83% align:start
And the campaign is
approaching two million views.

01:13:43.871 --> 01:13:45.406 position:38% line:89% align:start
(groans)

01:13:49.376 --> 01:13:52.379 position:24% line:83% align:start
So, how do you like
those figures?

01:13:54.114 --> 01:13:57.151 position:13% line:83% align:start
Now, that's the conclusion
of my presentation.

01:13:58.319 --> 01:14:00.120 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Hmm.
-(groans)

01:14:03.090 --> 01:14:04.992 position:30% line:89% align:start
Cut the stream.

01:14:05.025 --> 01:14:06.293 position:41% line:89% align:start
(gasps)

01:14:06.327 --> 01:14:08.495 position:41% line:89% align:start
(sighs)

01:14:08.529 --> 01:14:11.465 position:10% line:83% align:start
I'm afraid your little stunt
has failed.

01:14:11.498 --> 01:14:14.368 position:10% line:83% align:start
As such, you are to clear out
your desk immediately.

01:14:15.970 --> 01:14:18.372 position:10% line:89% align:start
There's no profit in dreams.

01:14:19.340 --> 01:14:21.375 position:21% line:89% align:start
(shuddering breaths)

01:14:27.881 --> 01:14:30.184 position:13% line:89% align:start
But why all the long faces?

01:14:30.217 --> 01:14:32.453 position:35% line:83% align:start
You put on
quite an entertaining show.

01:14:32.486 --> 01:14:34.455 position:21% line:89% align:start
You should be proud.

01:14:34.488 --> 01:14:36.290 position:24% line:89% align:start
Oh! Mr. President!

01:14:36.323 --> 01:14:39.226 position:13% line:89% align:start
Hurry! Turn off the stream!

01:14:39.260 --> 01:14:42.096 position:10% line:83% align:start
A certain someone informed me
of this, and I'm glad they did.

01:14:42.129 --> 01:14:43.831 position:30% line:89% align:start
(clears throat)

01:14:43.864 --> 01:14:45.165 position:30% line:89% align:start
I was watching.

01:14:45.199 --> 01:14:47.301 position:21% line:83% align:start
You know, it's by far
the best presentation

01:14:47.334 --> 01:14:49.036 position:16% line:89% align:start
I've seen in a long time.

01:14:49.069 --> 01:14:50.871 position:24% line:83% align:start
And it took resolve
and great courage

01:14:50.904 --> 01:14:53.474 position:16% line:89% align:start
in order to pull it off.

01:14:53.507 --> 01:14:56.844 position:24% line:83% align:start
This little project
has a lot of potential.

01:14:56.877 --> 01:14:59.213 position:19% line:83% align:start
We'll invest ten times
the crowdfunding amount.

01:14:59.246 --> 01:15:00.848 position:27% line:89% align:start
How's that sound?

01:15:00.881 --> 01:15:02.483 position:38% line:83% align:start
-(gasps)
-But, sir!

01:15:02.516 --> 01:15:06.186 position:10% line:83% align:start
You're using past indices as
indicators of potential growth.

01:15:06.220 --> 01:15:08.822 position:24% line:83% align:start
But you're ignoring
a very important element.

01:15:08.856 --> 01:15:10.524 position:27% line:89% align:start
What do you mean?

01:15:13.627 --> 01:15:15.362 position:35% line:5% align:start
PRESIDENT:
Take a look at this.

01:15:15.396 --> 01:15:17.598 position:5% line:5% align:start
Notice the spike in the funding.

01:15:17.631 --> 01:15:19.833 position:16% line:83% align:start
Any of you want to guess
what happened at that moment

01:15:19.867 --> 01:15:22.403 position:19% line:89% align:start
to motivate that spike?

01:15:22.436 --> 01:15:25.172 position:21% line:83% align:start
It's the moment when
Gene Fini and Alan Gardner

01:15:25.205 --> 01:15:26.940 position:33% line:83% align:start
were pouring
their hearts out to us.

01:15:29.410 --> 01:15:32.146 position:16% line:83% align:start
Assessing potential means
looking towards the future.

01:15:34.381 --> 01:15:36.150 position:10% line:89% align:start
By investing in their dreams,

01:15:36.183 --> 01:15:38.419 position:27% line:83% align:start
they're investing
in their future.

01:15:39.186 --> 01:15:41.221 position:35% line:89% align:start
Even so...

01:15:41.255 --> 01:15:43.190 position:13% line:89% align:start
And Nyallywood Bank invests

01:15:43.223 --> 01:15:45.225 position:24% line:83% align:start
in people who will
invest in their dreams.

01:15:45.259 --> 01:15:46.994 position:24% line:89% align:start
That is our motto.

01:15:47.027 --> 01:15:49.330 position:38% line:83% align:start
Hold on,
since when is that our motto?

01:15:49.363 --> 01:15:50.864 position:35% line:83% align:start
-Since now.
-Huh?

01:15:52.066 --> 01:15:56.236 position:10% line:83% align:start
And, Alan, you've got a very
bright future ahead of you.

01:15:56.270 --> 01:15:58.238 position:33% line:89% align:start
♪ <i>Whoa, oh</i> ♪

01:15:58.272 --> 01:15:59.940 position:24% line:89% align:start
(shuddering breath)

01:15:59.973 --> 01:16:01.041 position:33% line:89% align:start
♪ <i>Whoa, oh</i> ♪

01:16:01.075 --> 01:16:02.576 position:38% line:89% align:start
Oh, yes!

01:16:03.944 --> 01:16:05.579 position:33% line:83% align:start
-♪ <i>Whoa, oh</i> ♪
-Oh. (chuckles)

01:16:06.980 --> 01:16:08.248 position:33% line:89% align:start
♪ <i>Whoa, oh</i> ♪

01:16:08.282 --> 01:16:10.250 position:33% line:89% align:start
Nicely done.

01:16:10.284 --> 01:16:11.885 position:19% line:89% align:start
Thank you so much, sir.

01:16:11.919 --> 01:16:14.088 position:38% line:89% align:start
Oh, man.

01:16:14.121 --> 01:16:17.091 position:7% line:83% align:start
I can't remember the last time
we've had such a crazy meeting.

01:16:17.124 --> 01:16:18.892 position:33% line:83% align:start
It reminds me
of back when the president

01:16:18.926 --> 01:16:21.261 position:10% line:89% align:start
was still a junior executive.

01:16:21.295 --> 01:16:24.264 position:33% line:83% align:start
We'll invest!
Ah, that was thrilling!

01:16:24.298 --> 01:16:26.533 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

01:16:36.577 --> 01:16:38.412 position:13% line:89% align:start
I really appreciate you all

01:16:38.445 --> 01:16:40.614 position:16% line:83% align:start
for coming back to shoot
this additional scene.

01:16:40.647 --> 01:16:43.584 position:35% line:77% align:start
-(cheering)
-MAN: We wouldn't
miss it for the world!

01:16:43.617 --> 01:16:45.319 position:21% line:77% align:start
-MARTIN: Why are you
standing around?
-(grunts)

01:16:45.352 --> 01:16:46.653 position:30% line:83% align:start
Everyone's here
because we've got

01:16:46.687 --> 01:16:48.322 position:5% line:89% align:start
a crucial scene to shoot, right?

01:16:51.258 --> 01:16:53.227 position:33% line:89% align:start
Oh. Everyone.

01:16:53.260 --> 01:16:55.229 position:24% line:89% align:start
Thank you so much!

01:16:55.262 --> 01:16:57.998 position:13% line:83% align:start
The scene we'll be shooting
is a flashback

01:16:58.031 --> 01:17:00.401 position:19% line:83% align:start
to when D'Albert loses
his family.

01:17:00.434 --> 01:17:02.336 position:16% line:89% align:start
So who's playing my wife?

01:17:02.369 --> 01:17:03.504 position:41% line:83% align:start
MYSTIA:
That would be me.

01:17:04.705 --> 01:17:07.040 position:41% line:83% align:start
MARTIN:
Wow.

01:17:07.074 --> 01:17:10.177 position:21% line:83% align:start
I'm Martin Braddock,
and the best actor in the world.

01:17:10.210 --> 01:17:12.279 position:7% line:89% align:start
Want to add me to your socials?

01:17:12.312 --> 01:17:14.148 position:19% line:83% align:start
Sorry, but I don't have
a smartphone.

01:17:14.181 --> 01:17:16.316 position:24% line:83% align:start
Hmm? Wait a second.
We've met before.

01:17:16.350 --> 01:17:17.651 position:7% line:89% align:start
I don't see how that could be.

01:17:17.684 --> 01:17:19.653 position:38% line:89% align:start
Amazing.

01:17:19.686 --> 01:17:21.488 position:24% line:83% align:start
I would never know
that was Mystia.

01:17:21.522 --> 01:17:23.357 position:21% line:89% align:start
Well, you better not.

01:17:23.390 --> 01:17:26.160 position:13% line:83% align:start
All thanks to Nyallywood's
top prosthetic makeup artist.

01:17:28.061 --> 01:17:30.531 position:10% line:83% align:start
By the way, don't tell anyone
that it's her.

01:17:30.564 --> 01:17:33.200 position:19% line:83% align:start
Also, she wants to use
a pseudonym in the credits.

01:17:33.233 --> 01:17:35.235 position:19% line:83% align:start
Why? Is she embarrassed
by the role?

01:17:35.269 --> 01:17:37.438 position:30% line:89% align:start
It's not that.

01:17:37.471 --> 01:17:40.207 position:41% line:83% align:start
MYSTIA:
I'll do it under one condition.

01:17:40.240 --> 01:17:43.110 position:27% line:83% align:start
No one must know
that it's me, okay?

01:17:43.143 --> 01:17:45.446 position:16% line:83% align:start
Do you not like the part
or something? Oh...

01:17:45.479 --> 01:17:47.448 position:19% line:89% align:start
Oh, no, it's not that.

01:17:47.481 --> 01:17:50.083 position:16% line:83% align:start
And it's not that I don't
want to make a movie

01:17:50.117 --> 01:17:52.453 position:19% line:83% align:start
with Gene and Natalie,
'cause I do.

01:17:52.486 --> 01:17:56.056 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>And I'm sure I will one day,</i>
 <i>but...</i>

01:17:58.158 --> 01:18:00.727 position:16% line:83% align:start
...when that time comes,
I want to play the lead.

01:18:00.761 --> 01:18:02.763 position:27% line:89% align:start
 <i>And until then,</i>

01:18:02.797 --> 01:18:05.999 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>I don't want to appear</i>
 <i>in any of Gene's movies.</i>

01:18:06.033 --> 01:18:09.036 position:24% line:83% align:start
You've got a deal.
I'll make it work.

01:18:09.069 --> 01:18:11.171 position:10% line:83% align:start
Hair and makeup will make you
completely unrecognizable.

01:18:11.205 --> 01:18:12.105 position:38% line:83% align:start
 <i>MYSTIA:</i>
 <i>Great.</i>

01:18:13.707 --> 01:18:15.342 position:44% line:83% align:start
GENE:
Miss Pompo?

01:18:16.510 --> 01:18:18.278 position:7% line:89% align:start
Well, hurry up and get to work!

01:18:18.312 --> 01:18:20.214 position:38% line:89% align:start
(grunts)

01:18:20.247 --> 01:18:21.682 position:38% line:83% align:start
-(groans)
-♪ <i>Whoa, oh</i> ♪

01:18:21.715 --> 01:18:23.217 position:35% line:89% align:start
And action!

01:18:23.250 --> 01:18:25.085 position:33% line:89% align:start
♪ <i>Whoa, oh</i> ♪

01:18:25.118 --> 01:18:27.154 position:41% line:83% align:start
 <i>GENE:</i>
 <i>And so,</i>

01:18:27.187 --> 01:18:29.089 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>thanks to Pompo's</i>
 <i>amazing skill as a producer,</i>

01:18:29.122 --> 01:18:31.091 position:30% line:83% align:start
 <i>not to mention</i>
 <i>the crew's efforts,</i>

01:18:31.124 --> 01:18:33.427 position:5% line:89% align:start
 <i>we managed to finish the movie.</i>

01:18:35.629 --> 01:18:37.564 position:35% line:83% align:start
-(knocking)
-NATALIE: Excuse me.

01:18:37.598 --> 01:18:39.299 position:19% line:89% align:start
Director Gene? (gasps)

01:18:39.333 --> 01:18:41.502 position:38% line:89% align:start
So messy!

01:18:41.535 --> 01:18:43.737 position:16% line:89% align:start
Uh, hey, there, Natalie.

01:18:43.770 --> 01:18:45.606 position:35% line:83% align:start
Mystia said
you were busy editing,

01:18:45.639 --> 01:18:47.074 position:19% line:89% align:start
so I brought you food.

01:18:47.107 --> 01:18:48.709 position:13% line:89% align:start
I'm just gonna leave it...

01:18:48.742 --> 01:18:51.345 position:21% line:83% align:start
Whoa! What happened?
You look like a panda!

01:18:51.378 --> 01:18:54.081 position:35% line:83% align:start
Uh, right.
I haven't slept much.

01:18:54.114 --> 01:18:56.583 position:27% line:83% align:start
H-How much sleep
do you have to miss

01:18:56.617 --> 01:18:58.385 position:19% line:89% align:start
to get bags like that?

01:18:58.418 --> 01:19:00.087 position:24% line:89% align:start
I can't really say.

01:19:00.120 --> 01:19:02.089 position:27% line:83% align:start
